<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;7.1
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Definitions.&#160; For the purposes of this
<B>
	Article&nbsp;7
</B>
	with respect to Taxes, the following terms shall have the meanings set forth below:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Assessed Valuation
</B>
	&#148; shall mean the amount for which the Building is assessed pursuant to the applicable provisions of the City Charter and the Administrative Code of New York, or any successor Requirements, for the purpose of imposition of Taxes.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Intentionally Omitted.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Base Taxes
</B>
	&#148; are defined in
<B>
	Article&nbsp;1
</B>
	.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(d)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Comparison Year
</B>
	&#148; shall mean each Tax Year all or a portion of which occurs during the Term, commencing with the Tax Year immediately following the Base Tax Year.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(e)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	&#147;Statement
</B>
	&#148; shall mean a written statement containing a comparison of (i)&nbsp;the Base Taxes and the Taxes for any Comparison Year.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(f)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Tax Year
</B>
	&#148; shall mean the twelve month period from July&nbsp;1 through June&nbsp;30 (or such other period as hereinafter may be duly adopted by the City of New York as its fiscal year for real estate tax purpose).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(g)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Taxes
</B>
	&#148; shall mean (i)&nbsp;all real estate taxes, assessments (including any ICAP benefits and any assessments made as a result of the Building being within a business improvement), and other governmental levies, impositions or charges, whether general, special, ordinary, extraordinary, foreseen or unforeseen, which may be assessed, levied or imposed upon all or any part of the Real Property, and (ii)&nbsp;all expenses (including reasonable attorneys&#146; fees and disbursements and experts&#146; and other witnesses&#146; fees) actually incurred in contesting any of the foregoing or the Assessed Valuation of the Building (such expenses shall be included in&#160; Base Taxes if incurred during the Base Tax Year, or included in Taxes if incurred in a Comparison Year).&#160; Taxes shall not include (x)&nbsp;fines, interest or penalties together with any interest or costs with respect to the foregoing incurred by Landlord as a result of Landlord&#146;s late payment of Taxes or failure to pay any Taxes required to be paid, (y)&nbsp;capital levy, franchise, transfer, gift, inheritance, succession, estate or net municipal, state or federal income taxes imposed upon Landlord or tenants of the Building, or (z)&nbsp;unincorporated business taxes, income or profit tax, or any transfer or mortgage recording tax imposed upon any owner of the Real Property or Building. If Landlord elects to pay any assessment in annual installments, then (i)&nbsp;such assessment shall be deemed to have been so divided and to be payable in the maximum number of installments permitted by law, and (ii)&nbsp;there shall be deemed included in Taxes for each Comparison Year the installments of such assessment becoming payable during such Comparison Year.&#160; If at any time the methods of taxation prevailing on the Commencement Date shall be altered so that in lieu of or as an addition to the whole or any part of Taxes, there shall be assessed, levied or imposed (1)&nbsp;a tax, assessment, levy, imposition or charge based on the income or rents received from the Building whether or not wholly or partially as a capital levy or otherwise, (2)&nbsp;a tax, assessment, levy, imposition or charge measured by or based in whole or in part upon all or any part of the Building and imposed upon Landlord, (3)&nbsp;a license fee measured by the rents, or (4)&nbsp;any other tax, assessment, levy, imposition, charge or license fee however described or imposed, then to the extent the same shall be similarly treated as Taxes
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
	21
<A NAME="A2231003ZEX-10_17_HTM_1015-2-KU-05_PB_21_113215_5796">
</A>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">

<!-- ZEQ.=1,SEQ=24,EFW="2231003",CP="2U, INC.",DN="3",CHK=988795,FOLIO='21',FILE="DISK131:[17ZAA2.17ZAA11502]1015-2-KU-05_ZAA11502.CHC",USER="HYUNG",CD='FEB 23 12:02 2017' -->
<A NAME="eolPage226"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	by owners of Comparable Buildings all such alternative or additional taxes, assessments, levies, impositions, charges or license fees or the part thereof so measured or based shall be deemed to be Taxes.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;7.2
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Tenant&#146;s Tax Payment.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	If the Taxes payable for any Tax Year or portion of a Tax Year beginning with the Tax Year commencing immediately following the Base Tax Year, Tenant shall pay to Landlord Tenant&#146;s Proportionate Share of such excess (&#147;
<B>
	Tenant&#146;s Tax Payment
</B>
	&#148;) as Additional Rent. For each Comparison Year, Landlord shall furnish to Tenant a written statement setting forth Landlord&#146;s reasonable estimate of Tenant&#146;s Tax Payment for such Tax Year (the &#147;
<B>
	Tax Estimate
</B>
	&#148;).&#160; Tenant shall pay to Landlord on the 1st day of each month prior to and during such Comparison Year (but not more than six (6)&nbsp;months prior to the start of such Comparison Year) an amount equal to 1/12th of the Tax Estimate for such Tax Year (&#147;
<B>
	Tenant&#146;s Monthly Tax Payment
</B>
	&#148;).&#160; If Landlord furnishes a Tax Estimate for a Comparison Year subsequent to the commencement thereof, then (i)&nbsp;until the 1st day of the month following the month in which the Tax Estimate is furnished to Tenant, Tenant shall pay to Landlord on the 1st day of each month an amount equal to the monthly sum payable by Tenant to Landlord under this
<B>
	Section&nbsp;7.2(a)
</B>
	&nbsp;for the last month of the preceding Comparison Year; (ii)&nbsp;promptly after the Tax Estimate is furnished to Tenant or together therewith, Landlord shall give written notice to Tenant stating whether the installments of the Tax Estimate previously made for such Comparison Year were greater or less than the installments of the Tax Estimate to be made for such Comparison Year in accordance with the Tax Estimate, and (x)&nbsp;if there shall be a deficiency, Tenant shall pay the amount thereof within 30 days after receipt of written demand, or (y)&nbsp;if there shall have been an overpayment, Landlord shall credit the amount thereof against subsequent payments of Rent next coming due hereunder (or if there shall be no subsequent payments of Rent next coming due, Landlord shall pay to Tenant the amount of such overpayment within thirty (30) days; and (iii)&nbsp;on the 1st day of the month following ten (10)&nbsp;Business Days&#146; notice, and on the 1st day of each month thereafter throughout the remainder of such Comparison Year (and the next comparison year until a new estimate or statement is provided), Tenant shall pay to Landlord an amount equal to 1/12th of the Tax Estimate.&#160; Landlord may, at any time, furnish to Tenant a revised Tax Estimate for such Comparison Year, and in such case, Tenant&#146;s Tax Payment for such Comparison Year shall be adjusted and any deficiencies paid (including, without limitations as a result of late billing of Tenant) or overpayments credited, as the case may be, substantially in the same manner as provided in the preceding sentence.&#160; Within 180 days after the end of each Comparison Year, Landlord shall furnish to Tenant a Statement of Taxes applicable to Tenant&#146;s Tax Payment payable for such Comparison Year together with copies of the actual Tax bills used in connection with such calculation (if received), and (A)&nbsp;if such Statement shall show that the sums so paid by Tenant were less than Tenant&#146;s Tax Payment due for such Comparison Year, Tenant shall pay to Landlord the amount of such deficiency within 30 days after delivery of the Statement to Tenant, or (B)&nbsp;if such Statement shall show that the sums so paid by Tenant were more than such Tenant&#146;s Tax Payment, Landlord shall credit such overpayment against subsequent payments of Rent next coming due, if any (or if there shall be no subsequent payments of Rent next coming due, Landlord shall pay to Tenant the amount of such overpayment within thirty (30) days).&#160; If there shall be any increase in the Taxes for any Tax Year during the Term, whether during or after such Tax Year, or if there shall be any decrease in the Taxes for any Tax Year, Tenant&#146;s Tax Payment for such Comparison Year shall be appropriately adjusted and any deficiencies paid or overpayments credited (or repaid), as the case may be, substantially in the same manner as provided in the preceding sentence.&#160; Landlord agrees that the Base Tax Year shall be the first Tax Year that ICAP benefits are obtained and applicable for the Real Property. Until a Base Tax Year is so determined, Tenant
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
	22
<A NAME="A2231003ZEX-10_17_HTM_1015-2-KU-05_PB_22_113229_2897">
</A>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="100%" NOSHADE ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="COLOR:#010101;">
</DIV>

<!-- ZEQ.=1,SEQ=25,EFW="2231003",CP="2U, INC.",DN="3",CHK=714359,FOLIO='22',FILE="DISK131:[17ZAA2.17ZAA11502]1015-2-KU-05_ZAA11502.CHC",USER="HYUNG",CD='FEB 23 12:02 2017' -->
<A NAME="eolPage227"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	shall have no obligation to pay Tenant&#146;s Proportionate Share of any Taxes, unless ICAP benefits are not obtained (or are obtained but withdrawn) on or before the 2020/2021 Tax Year, then in such case the Base Tax Year shall be the 2020/2021 Tax Year.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Only Landlord may institute proceedings to reduce the Assessed Valuation of the Building and the filing of any such proceeding by Tenant without Landlord&#146;s consent shall constitute an Event of Default.&#160; If the Base Taxes are reduced, the Additional Rent previously paid or payable on account of Tenant&#146;s Tax Payment hereunder for all Comparison Years shall be recomputed on the basis of such reduction, and Tenant shall pay to Landlord, within thirty (30) days after demand therefore, any deficiency between the amount of such Additional Rent previously computed and paid by Tenant to Landlord, and the amount due as a result of such recomputation.&#160; If the Base Taxes are increased, then Landlord shall either pay to Tenant, or at Landlord&#146;s election, credit against subsequent payments of Rent due, if any (or if there shall be no subsequent payments of Rent next coming due, Landlord shall pay to Tenant the amount of such overpayment within twenty (20) Business Days), the amount by which such Additional Rent previously paid on account of Tenant&#146;s Tax Payment exceeds the amount actually due as a result of such recomputation.&#160; If Landlord receives a refund of Taxes for any Comparison Year, Landlord shall, at its election, either pay to Tenant, or credit against subsequent payments of Rent due hereunder (or if there shall be no subsequent payments of Rent next coming due, Landlord shall pay to Tenant the amount of such overpayment within twenty (20) Business Days), an amount equal to Tenant&#146;s Proportionate Share of the refund, net of any reasonable, actual, out of pocket expenses incurred by Landlord in achieving such refund, which amount shall not exceed Tenant&#146;s Tax Payment paid for such Comparison Year. Landlord shall not be obligated to file any application or institute any proceeding seeking a reduction in Taxes or the Assessed Valuation. The benefit of any exemption or abatement relating to all or any part of the Building shall accrue to the benefit of Landlord provided, however, that Taxes for the Base Tax Year and all Comparison Years shall be computed by taking into account any such exemption or abatement.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Tenant shall be responsible for any applicable occupancy or rent tax now in effect or hereafter enacted to the extent Tenant is primarily liable for same or if applicable to Tenant&#146;s use and occupancy of the Premises and, if such tax is payable by Landlord, Tenant shall pay such amounts to Landlord within thirty (30) days following Tenant&#146;s receipt of Landlord&#146;s written request therefor.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(d)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Tenant shall be obligated to make Tenant&#146;s Tax Payment regardless of whether Tenant may be exempt from the payment of any taxes as the result of any reduction, abatement, or exemption from Taxes granted or agreed to by any Governmental Authority, or by reason of Tenant&#146;s diplomatic or other tax exempt status.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;7.3
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Operating Expense Definitions.&#160;&#160; For the purposes of this
<B>
	Article&nbsp;7
</B>
	with respect to Operating Expenses, the following terms shall have the meanings set forth below:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Base Operating Expenses
</B>
	&#148; shall mean the Operating Expenses as stated in Article&nbsp;1 for the &#147;Base Expense Year&#148;.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Comparison Year
</B>
	&#148; shall mean with respect to Operating Expenses, each calendar year commencing subsequent to the first day of the Base Expense Year.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Operating Expenses
</B>
	&#148; shall mean the aggregate of all costs and expenses paid or incurred by or on behalf of Landlord in connection with the ownership,
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
	23
<A NAME="A2231003ZEX-10_17_HTM_1015-2-KU-05_PB_23_113258_3020">
</A>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="100%" NOSHADE ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="COLOR:#010101;">
</DIV>
</DIV>
<!-- ZEQ.=1,SEQ=26,EFW="2231003",CP="2U, INC.",DN="3",CHK=783168,FOLIO='23',FILE="DISK131:[17ZAA2.17ZAA11502]1015-2-KU-05_ZAA11502.CHC",USER="HYUNG",CD='FEB 23 12:02 2017' -->
<A NAME="eolPage228"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	operation, repair and maintenance of the Real Property, including the rental value of Landlord&#146;s Building office and capital improvements to the Building&#160; incurred after the Base Expense Year only if such capital improvement either (i)&nbsp;is reasonably intended to result in a reduction in Operating Expenses (as for example, a labor-saving improvement) provided, the amount included in Operating Expenses in any Comparison Year from and after the Commencement Date shall not exceed an amount equal to the savings reasonably anticipated to result from the installation and operation of such improvement, and/or (ii)&nbsp;is made during any Comparison Year to cause the Building to be in compliance with Requirements enacted after the Commencement Date.&#160; Such capital improvements shall be amortized (with interest at the Base Rate) on a straight-line basis over such period as Landlord shall reasonably determine in accordance with GAAP or other customary and uniform ownership accounting practices, and the amount included in Operating Expenses in any Comparison Year shall be equal to the annual amortized amount.&#160; Operating Expenses shall not include any Excluded Expenses.&#160; If during all or part of the Base Expense Year or any Comparison Year, Landlord shall not furnish any particular item(s)&nbsp;of work or service (which would otherwise constitute an Operating Expense) to any leasable portions of the Building for any reason, then, for purposes of computing Operating Expenses for such period, the amount included in Operating Expenses for such period shall be increased by an amount equal to the costs and expenses that would have been reasonably incurred by Landlord during such period if Landlord had furnished such item(s)&nbsp;of work or service to such portion of the Building. In determining the amount of Operating Expenses for the Base Expense Year or any Comparison Year, if less than 100% of the Building rentable area is occupied by tenants at any time during the Base Expense Year or any such Comparison Year, Operating Expenses shall be determined for the Base Expense Year or such Comparison Year to be an amount equal to the like expenses which would normally be expected to be incurred had such occupancy been 100% throughout the Base Expense Year or such Comparison Year.&#160; For each calendar year or portion thereof occurring during the Term (including the Base Expense Year), Operating Expenses shall include a management fee of three percent (3%) of all rents and other charges made to and/or collected from all office tenants of the Building during such calendar year (or which would have been made to and/or collected if the Building was one hundred percent (100%) occupied with office tenants paying rent as provided under their respective leases for the entire year, assuming for purposes of this calculation that rents and other charges payable in respect of any unoccupied office space would be payable at the average rate of rents and other charges payable in respect of all occupied office space, in each case on a per rentable square foot basis, for such calendar year), but excepting in any event rent and other charges collected from tenants or other permitted occupants with respect to Building retail spaces, the provisions of this clause to apply regardless of the actual management fee, or increases in the actual management fee, incurred by Landlord during such calendar year or portion thereof (i.e., any management fee paid by Landlord in excess of the management fee permitted under this clause shall not be an Operating Expense).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(d)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;Excluded Expenses&#148; shall mean:&#160; (a)&nbsp;Taxes; (b)&nbsp;franchise or income taxes imposed upon Landlord; (c)&nbsp;mortgage amortization and interest; (d)&nbsp;leasing commissions; (e)&nbsp;the cost of tenant installations and decorations incurred in connection with preparing space for any Building tenant, including work letters and concessions; (f)&nbsp;the cost of the Base Building Work, (g)&nbsp;any amounts payable for rent under Superior Leases, if any except similar operating expenses; (h)&nbsp;wages, salaries and benefits paid to any persons above the grade of property manager or chief engineer and their immediate supervisor; (i)&nbsp;legal and accounting fees relating to (A)&nbsp;disputes with tenants, prospective tenants or other occupants of the Building, (B)&nbsp;disputes with purchasers, prospective purchasers, mortgagees or prospective mortgagees of the Building or the Real Property or any part of either, or (C)&nbsp;negotiations of leases, contracts of sale or mortgages; (j)&nbsp;costs of services provided to other tenants of the Building on a &#147;rent-inclusion&#148;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	basis which are not provided to Tenant on such basis in which event such costs shall be excluded from Base Expenses (provided if such services are no longer provided on a rent-inclusion basis, such cost shall be retroactively included in Base Operating Expenses if not then included; (k)&nbsp;costs that are reimbursed out of insurance, warranty or condemnation proceeds, or which are reimbursed by Tenant or other tenants other than pursuant to an expense escalation clause; (l)&nbsp;costs in the nature of penalties or fines; (m)&nbsp;costs for services, supplies or repairs paid to any related entity in excess of costs that would be payable in an &#147;arm&#146;s length&#148; or unrelated situation for comparable services, supplies or repairs; (r)&nbsp;costs incurred in connection with the removal, encapsulation or other treatment of asbestos or any other Hazardous Materials existing in the Building or on the Real Property as of the date hereof, and defined as a Hazardous Material as of the date hereof, and (s)&nbsp;rental cost of items which (if purchased) would be capitalized and excluded from Operating Expenses; (t)&nbsp;costs in connection with the creation or amendment of any Superior Lease (including without limitation any legal fees and expenses, third party reports, title policies and compliance costs and expenses); (u)&nbsp;the portion of any fee or expenditure paid to any Affiliate of Landlord which exceeds the amount which would be paid for comparable services and/or goods in the absence of such relationship; (v)&nbsp;auditing fees in connection with tenant (including Tenant) disputes; (w)&nbsp;depreciation or amortization, except as provided in the definition of Operating Expenses above; (x)&nbsp;costs relating to withdrawal liability or unfunded pension liability under the Multi-Employer Pension Plan Act or other Requirement; (y)&nbsp;expenditures for repairing and/or replacing any defect in any work performed by or on behalf of Landlord pursuant to the provisions of this Lease or elsewhere in the Building, in each case to the extent expenditures for such repairs and/or replacements are recovered by warranty for such work; (z)&nbsp;any fees, dues or contributions to charitable organizations, civic organizations, political parties or political action committees; (aa) costs and expenses resulting from the gross negligence or willful misconduct of Landlord, any Landlord Party or any of Landlord&#146;s contractors and any damages and attorneys&#146; fees and disbursements and other costs in connection with any judgment, settlement or arbitration award resulting from any tort liability of Landlord, any Landlord Party or any of Landlord&#146;s contractors; (bb) costs and expenses incurred by Landlord in connection with any obligation of Landlord to indemnify any tenant (including Tenant) pursuant to its lease or otherwise or which solely result from Landlord&#146;s or any other tenant&#146;s breach of a lease and except to the extent such cost would otherwise be includable in Operating Expenses; (cc) costs relating to any conversion to of the Building to a condominium or dissolution of such condominium; (dd)&nbsp;costs of purchasing, insuring, repairing or removing works of fine art and in excess of customary Building artwork; (ee)&nbsp;reserves for bad debt, rental loss, or any similar charge not involving payment of money to third parties; (ff) costs of organizing or maintaining Landlord as an entity, such as annual registration fees for limited liability companies or partnerships, and legal and accounting fees in organizing or maintaining Landlord as an entity; (gg) costs to correct any condition that is in material violation of any representation, warranty or covenant of Landlord made in this Lease, but only if costs relating to the item to be corrected are not otherwise includable in Operating Expenses; (hh) costs that are otherwise expressly excluded from Operating Expenses pursuant to the express terms of this Lease; (ii)&nbsp;omitted; (jj) the cost of any repair, replacement or restoration or other work occasioned by fire, windstorm or other casualty insured under a

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	standard &#147;all risk&#148; policy of insurance (regardless of whether Landlord has in fact maintained such insurance) other than commercially reasonable deductible amounts or self-retention, in each case consistent with amounts carried by landlords of comparable office buildings&#160; or the exercise by government authorities of the right of eminent domain (whether taking is total or partial) or condemnation, to the extent Landlord is compensated therefore and in either case, subject to the limitations on reimbursements for capital expenditures; (kk) costs incurred in connection with the financing or refinancing of the Real Property or any interest (direct or indirect) in Landlord, or a sale or transfer of all or any portion of the Real Property (including the acquisition or sale of air rights, transferable development rights, easements or other real property interests) or any interest therein or in any Person of whatever tier owing an interest therein (including without limitation any legal fees and expenses, third party reports, title policies and compliance costs and expenses);payments made to tenants or their landlords to take over leases;
</FONT>
	and (ll)&nbsp;the cost of capital improvements other than those expressly included in Operating Expenses pursuant to Article&nbsp;7.

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(e)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Statement
</B>
	&#148; with respect to Operating Expenses shall mean a reasonably detailed and customary statement containing a comparison of the Base Operating Expenses and the Operating Expenses for any Comparison Year, which shall include major categories of expenses and be reasonably similar to such statements provided at Comparable Buildings as reasonably determined by Landlord.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;7.4
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Tenant&#146;s Operating Payment.&#160; (a)&nbsp; If the Operating Expenses payable for any Comparison Year exceed the Base Operating Expenses, Tenant shall pay to Landlord Tenant&#146;s Proportionate Share of such excess (&#147;Tenant&#146;s Operating Payment&#148;).&#160; For each Comparison Year, Landlord shall furnish to Tenant a statement setting forth Landlord&#146;s reasonable estimate of Tenant&#146;s Operating Payment for such Comparison Year (the &#147;Expense Estimate&#148;).&#160; Tenant shall pay to Landlord on the 1st day of each month during such Comparison Year an amount equal to 1/12 of the Expense Estimate (&#147;Tenant&#146;s Monthly Operating Payment&#148;).&#160; If Landlord furnishes an Expense Estimate for a Comparison Year subsequent to the commencement thereof, then (i)&nbsp;until the 1st day of the month following the month in which the Expense Estimate is furnished to Tenant, Tenant shall pay to Landlord on the 1st day of each month an amount equal to the monthly sum payable by Tenant to Landlord under this Section&nbsp;7.4 during the last month of the preceding Comparison Year, (ii)&nbsp;promptly after the Expense Estimate is furnished to Tenant or together therewith, Landlord shall give notice to Tenant stating whether the installments of Tenant&#146;s Operating Payment previously made for such Comparison Year were greater or less than the installments of Tenant&#146;s Operating Payment to be made for such Comparison Year in accordance with the Expense Estimate, and (A)&nbsp;if there shall be a deficiency, Tenant shall pay the amount thereof within 30 days after demand therefor, or (B)&nbsp;if there shall have been an overpayment, Landlord shall credit the amount thereof against subsequent payments of Rent due hereunder, and (iii)&nbsp;on the 1st day of the month following the month in which the Expense Estimate is furnished to Tenant, and on the 1st day of each month thereafter throughout the remainder of such Comparison Year, Tenant shall pay to Landlord an amount equal to 1/12 of the Expense Estimate.(b)
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Landlord shall endeavor to furnish to Tenant a final Statement for the immediately preceding Comparison Year on or before July&nbsp;1st of each Comparison Year.&#160; If the Statement shows that the sums paid by Tenant under this Section&nbsp;7.4 exceeded the actual amount of Tenant&#146;s Operating Payment for such Comparison Year, Landlord shall credit the amount of such excess against subsequent payments of Rent due hereunder.&#160; If the Statement shows that the sums so paid by Tenant were less than Tenant&#146;s Operating Payment for such Comparison Year, Tenant shall pay the amount of such deficiency within 10 Business Days after delivery of the Statement to Tenant.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<A NAME="eolPage231"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;7.5
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Non-Waiver; Disputes
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Landlord&#146;s failure to render any Statement on a timely basis with respect to any Comparison Year shall not prejudice Landlord&#146;s right to thereafter render a Statement with respect to such Comparison Year or any subsequent Comparison Year, nor shall the rendering of a Statement prejudice Landlord&#146;s right to thereafter render a corrected Statement for that Comparison Year, provided, however, in no event shall Tenant have any liability hereunder with respect to any Statement or corrected Statement not delivered to Tenant within two (2)&nbsp;years following the Comparison Year in question, or earlier termination of the Lease (except for Taxes for a Comparison Year that are then being contested by Landlord in accordance with
<B>
	Section&nbsp;7.2 (b)
</B>
	, in which event the foregoing two (2)&nbsp;year period shall commence on the Expiration Date, or early termination date, as the case may be, and shall end on the date that a final determination is rendered by the Department of Taxation and Finance of the City of New York for the Comparison Year contested.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Each Statement sent to Tenant shall be conclusively binding upon Tenant unless Tenant (i)&nbsp;pays to Landlord when due the amount set forth in such Statement, without prejudice to Tenant&#146;s right to dispute such Statement, and (ii)&nbsp;within 120 days after such Statement is sent requests to review backup information in respect of such Statement, provided, however, that Tenant&#146;s right to review and/or dispute the Statement for the Base Expense Year shall be exercised, if at all, concurrently with Tenant&#146;s first review of the Statement for the first Comparison Year.&#160; Upon Tenant&#146;s request, Landlord shall provide Tenant or its representative any information as shall reasonably be necessary to enable Tenant to assess the accuracy of the Operating Expenses applicable to such Statement and, if applicable, the Operating Expenses for the Base Expense Year. Each Statement shall be conclusively binding upon Tenant unless Tenant (or its representative) shall, within 90 days after such information is provided to Tenant, send a written notice to Landlord objecting to such Statement and specifying the reasons for Tenant&#146;s claim that such Statement is incorrect. Tenant agrees that Tenant will not employ, in connection with any review or dispute under this Lease, any person or entity who is to be compensated in whole or in part, on a contingency fee basis. If the parties are unable to resolve any dispute as to the correctness of such Statement within 30 days following such notice of objection, either party may refer the issues raised to a nationally recognized independent public accounting firm mutually acceptable to Landlord and Tenant, and the decision of such accountants shall be conclusively binding upon Landlord and Tenant.&#160; In connection therewith, Tenant and such accountants shall execute and deliver to Landlord a confidentiality agreement, in form and substance reasonably satisfactory to Landlord, whereby such parties agree not to disclose to any third party any of the information obtained in connection with such review.&#160; Tenant shall pay the fees and expenses relating to such procedure, unless such accountants determine that Landlord overstated Operating Expenses by more than 5% for such Comparison Year, in which case Landlord shall pay such fees and expenses.&#160; Except as provided in this Section, Tenant shall have no right whatsoever to dispute by judicial proceeding or otherwise the accuracy of any Statement. If the parties hereto are unable to mutually agree to a nationally recognized accounting firm, then either party, on behalf of both, may request appointment of such accountants by the American Arbitration Association.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;7.6
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Proration.&#160; If the Commencement Date is not January&nbsp;1, the Additional Rent for the applicable Comparison Year shall be apportioned on the basis of the number of days in the year from the Commencement Date to the following December&nbsp;31.&#160; If the Expiration Date occurs on a date other than December&nbsp;31, any Additional Rent under this
<B>
	Article&nbsp;7
</B>
	for the Comparison Year in which such Expiration Date occurs shall be apportioned on the basis of the number of days in the year from January&nbsp;1 to the Expiration Date.&#160; Upon the expiration or earlier
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	termination of this Lease, any Additional Rent under this
<B>
	Article&nbsp;7
</B>
	shall be adjusted or paid within 30 days after submission of the Statement for the last Comparison Year.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;7.7
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	No Reduction in Rent.&#160; In no event shall any decrease in Taxes or Operating Expenses in any Comparison Year below the Base Taxes or Base Operating Expenses, respectfully, result in a reduction in the Fixed Rent or any other component of Additional Rent payable hereunder.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ARTICLE&nbsp;8
<BR>
	REQUIREMENTS OF LAW
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;8.1
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Compliance with Requirements.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Tenant&#146;s Compliance
</B>
	.&#160; Tenant, at its cost and expense, shall comply with all Requirements applicable to the Premises and/or Tenant&#146;s use or occupancy thereof, including, without limitation, the installation of a life safety system in the Premises from the point of connection into the base Building life safety system, in accordance with all applicable Requirements governing the installation, maintenance and operation of such system (subject to the terms of Article&nbsp;5 above) provided, however, that Tenant shall not be obligated to comply with any Requirements requiring any structural alterations to the Building or alterations to Building Systems beyond the point of connection to the Premises, unless the application of such Requirements arises from (i)&nbsp;the specific manner and nature of Tenant&#146;s use or occupancy of the Premises, as distinct from general office use, (ii)&nbsp;Alterations made by Tenant, (iii)&nbsp;a breach by Tenant of any of the provisions of this Lease, or (iv)&nbsp;the negligence or willful misconduct of Tenant.&#160; Subject to the provisions of
<B>
	Article&nbsp;12,
</B>
	any repairs or alterations required to be made by Tenant for compliance with applicable Requirements to the extent required&#160; by this
<B>
	Section&nbsp;8.1(a)
</B>
	&nbsp;shall be made at Tenant&#146;s expense (1)&nbsp;by Tenant in compliance with
<B>
	Article&nbsp;5
</B>
	if such repairs or alterations are nonstructural and do not affect any Building System outside of the Premises and to the extent such repairs or alterations do not affect areas outside the Premises, or (2)&nbsp;by Landlord if such repairs or alterations are structural or affect any Building System or to the extent such repairs or alterations affect areas outside the Premises, provided, however, the foregoing provisions of this
<B>
	Section&nbsp;8.1(a)
</B>
	&nbsp;shall not be construed to require Tenant to perform structural Alterations, unless the same are required due to clauses (i), (ii), or (iii)&nbsp;of the immediately preceding sentence.&#160; If Tenant obtains written notice or otherwise has actual knowledge of any failure to comply with any Requirements applicable to the Premises (where Tenant has a duty to comply with such Requirements), Tenant shall give Landlord prompt notice thereof. Tenant hereby agrees to indemnify Landlord for any actual costs, loss, injury, expense or fees (including reasonable attorneys&#146; fees) incurred by reason of such non-compliance that is the responsibility of Tenant as provided in this
<B>
	Section&nbsp;8.1(a)
</B>
	.&#160; If Tenant&#146;s occupancy of the Premises, based on Tenant&#146;s pro-rata share of any partial floor of a Building that it occupies violates the density requirements set forth in the existing TCO or Certificate of Occupancy for such Building for any full floor or the portion of such floor that it occupies, then Tenant shall either (i)&nbsp;modify the Building&#146;s TCO or&#160; Certificate of Occupancy, as the case may be, to permit such occupancy, or (ii)&nbsp;take all action necessary to put the Premises in compliance with such density requirements (i.e., if the TCO or Certificate of Occupancy permits 100 persons on a floor and Tenant occupies one-half of such floor, then Tenant shall not be permitted to have more than 50 people occupy such floor).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Hazardous Materials
</B>
	.&#160; Tenant shall not cause (or permit): (i)&nbsp;any Hazardous Materials to be brought into the Building, (ii)&nbsp;the storage or use of Hazardous Materials in or about the Building or the Premises (subject to the second sentence of this
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

	Section&nbsp;8.1[b]
</FONT>
</B>
	), in the case of clause&nbsp;(i)&nbsp;and (ii), and then in any manner other than in full compliance with any Requirements), or (iii)&nbsp;the escape, disposal or release of any Hazardous Materials&#160; brought into the premises by or through any Tenant Party within or in the vicinity of the Building (provided none of the foregoing shall apply to Hazardous Materials in the Building as of the Commencement Date).&#160; Nothing herein shall be deemed to prevent Tenant&#146;s use and storage of any Hazardous Materials customarily used in the ordinary course of Permitted Use or in connection with Alterations, provided such use is customary and in accordance with all Requirements and consistent with Building Standard.&#160; Tenant shall be responsible, at its expense, for all matters directly or indirectly based on, or arising or resulting from the presence of Hazardous Materials in the Building which is caused or permitted by a Tenant Party.&#160; Tenant shall provide to Landlord copies of all communications received by Tenant with respect to any Requirements relating to Hazardous Materials, and/or any claims made in connection therewith.&#160; Landlord or its agents may perform non-invasive environmental inspections of the Premises at all reasonable times upon not less than twenty-four (24) hours&#146; notice to Tenant (except in the case of an emergency, in which case the inspection may be performed at any time and without advance notice to Tenant); provided, that any such access by Landlord and/or its agents shall be subject to all the terms and conditions of this Lease, including using commercially reasonable efforts to minimize any interference with the conduct of Tenant&#146;s business in the Premises.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Landlord&#146;s Compliance
</B>
	.&#160; Landlord, at its cost and expense, shall comply with (or cause to be complied with) all Requirements applicable to the Common Areas and the Building which are not the obligation of Tenant in accordance with the terms hereof and/or the need for such compliance was not caused by Tenant, to the extent that non-compliance (i)&nbsp;would impair Tenant&#146;s use and occupancy of the Premises for the Permitted Use (as opposed to Tenant&#146;s particular manner of use of the Premises) and Tenant&#146;s Roof Deck Area for the RDA Permitted Uses, or (ii)&nbsp;would threaten the health and safety of Tenant and Tenant Parties, (iii)&nbsp;would delay Tenant&#146;s ability to start or finish any Alterations, (iv)&nbsp;would result in the imposition upon Tenant or any Tenant Party of civil or criminal penalties or (v)&nbsp;would violate any insurance policy maintained by Tenant or render the same null and void.&#160;&#160; Landlord represents that (A)&nbsp;the Premises on the Substantial Completion Date will be in compliance in all material respects with applicable laws and requirements of public authorities (including, without limitation, the ADA in respect of access thereto) having jurisdiction over the Building and (B)&nbsp;Tenant&#146;s Roof Deck Area on the Substantial Completion Date for Tenant&#146;s Roof Work and the Secondary Base Building Roof Work will be in compliance in all material respects with applicable laws and requirements of public authorities (including, without limitation, the ADA) having jurisdiction over the Building.&#160; For the avoidance of doubt, (i)&nbsp;Landlord shall have no obligation to obtain a public assembly permit in respect of Tenant&#146;s Roof Deck Area and/or in connection with the Roof Work, and (ii)&nbsp;whether or not a public assembly permit is obtained shall not affect the Commencement Date or Rent Commencement Date.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;

	(d)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Landlord&#146;s Insurance
</B>
	.&#160; Tenant shall not cause or knowingly permit any action or condition that would (i)&nbsp;invalidate or conflict with Landlord&#146;s insurance policies provided the same shall be commercially reasonable, (ii)&nbsp;violate applicable rules, regulations and guidelines of the Fire Department, Fire Insurance Rating Organization or any other authority having jurisdiction over the Building, (iii)&nbsp;cause an increase in the premiums of fire insurance for the Building over that payable with respect to Comparable Buildings (unless Tenant pays such increase), or (iv)&nbsp;result in Landlord&#146;s insurance companies&#146; refusing to insure the Building or any property therein in amounts and against risks as reasonably determined by Landlord. Landlord hereby represents that, to the best of Landlord&#146;s actual knowledge as of the date hereof, Tenant&#146;s use of the Premises for the Permitted Use and the Tenant&#146;s Roof Deck Area for the
</P>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

<B>

	(e)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

<B>
	Certain Violations
</B>
	&#160; If the existence of any violations of Requirements noted of record against the Real Property (other than any such violations created by any Tenant Party or which will be cured by Tenant by the performance of the Initial Installations) shall actually delay (or prevent) Tenant from obtaining any governmental permits, consents, approvals or other documentation required by Tenant for (A)&nbsp;the performance of any Initial Installation or Alteration affecting a full floor or more, or (B)&nbsp;the lawful occupancy of any portion of the Premises upon completion of any Initial Installations or Alterations affecting a full floor or more, therein (it being understood that the imposition of conditions by a Governmental Authority requiring the cure of any such violation as a condition precedent to obtaining any such governmental permits, consents, approvals or other documentation which shall so actually delay Tenant from obtaining any required governmental permits, consents, approvals or other documentations shall be deemed such a prevention or delay), then, upon the giving of notice by Tenant to Landlord of such prevention or delay and of the applicable violations, (x)&nbsp;Landlord shall promptly commence and thereafter diligently prosecute to completion the cure and removal of record of such violations, (y)&nbsp;Tenant shall be entitled to an abatement of rent equal to the Fixed Rent and Additional Rent allocable to the affected portion of the Premises for the period commencing on the date Tenant gives to Landlord notice of such&#160; prevention or delay and ending on the earlier of the (i)&nbsp;date Tenant is no longer prevented from obtaining such governmental permit, consent or approval (ii)&nbsp;the date Tenant obtains such governmental permit, consent or approval or a waiver of such requirement continuing thereafter for the duration of such prevention or delay, and (iii)&nbsp;the date Tenant commences or continues the performance of such affected work or occupies the Premises for the conduct of business.

	Section&nbsp;8.2
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Tenant Fire and Life Safety; Sprinkler.&#160; If the Fire Insurance Rating Organization or any Governmental Authority or any of Landlord&#146;s insurers requires any modifications and/or alterations be made or any additional equipment be supplied in connection with the sprinkler system or fire alarm and life-safety system serving the Premises or Building by reason of Tenant&#146;s manner of use or occupancy of the Premises (as opposed to mere Office Use), or any Alterations performed by Tenant, or Tenant&#146;s Property, or other contents of the Premises (which are not customary office contents), Landlord (to the extent outside of the Premises) or Tenant (to the extent within the Premises) shall make such modifications and/or Alterations, and supply such additional equipment, in either case at Tenant&#146;s cost and expense.
</P>

	Landlord Fire and Life Safety; Sprinkler.&#160; Landlord shall maintain, repair and replace, if necessary, at Landlord&#146;s sole cost and expense, the Building Systems situated outside of the Premises, including, but not limited to, the main sprinkler valves and risers, base building fire alarm systems and devices. In addition, Landlord shall also provide sufficient points of connection to the base Building fire alarm system for Tenant&#146;s fire alarm input and output devices as well as for Tenant sub-systems (e.g., pre-action sprinkler system), in compliance with all applicable New York City code Requirements. &#160;Any modification to the base Building infrastructure shall be at Landlord&#146;s sole cost and expense, unless such modification is necessitated by reason of Tenant&#146;s Alteration(s), gross negligence or willful misconduct.&#160; In

<A NAME="eolPage234"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	connection with Tenant&#146;s performance of any Alterations, Tenant shall not be required, but shall be permitted, to perform daily drain-downs of the sprinkler system, at Tenant&#146;s cost and expense in accordance with all applicable Requirements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ARTICLE&nbsp;9
<BR>
	SUBORDINATION
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;9.1
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Subordination and Attornment.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	This Lease is subject and subordinate to all Mortgages and Superior Leases (now and/or hereafter), and, at the request of any Mortgagee or Lessor, Tenant shall attorn to such Mortgagee or Lessor, its successors in interest or any purchaser in a foreclosure sale. Notwithstanding the foregoing, provided that this Lease shall then be in full force and effect and no Event of Default shall then exist, then as a condition to Tenant&#146;s obligation to subordinate this Lease to any future Mortgage or Superior Lease, Landlord shall secure from any future Mortgagee or Superior Lessor, as applicable, at no cost or expense of Landlord, a subordination, non-disturbance and attornment agreement (&#147;
<B>
	SNDA
</B>
	&#148;) in a reasonable and customary form (and Tenant agrees that the form of SNDA attached hereto as
<B>
<U STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Exhibit&nbsp;N
</U>
</B>
	or a form substantially comparable thereto (the &#147;
<B>
	Approved SNDA Form
</B>
	&#148;) is reasonable and customary) provided that Tenant shall execute and deliver any such SNDA in such Approved SNDA Form&nbsp;within ten (10)&nbsp;days following Landlord&#146;s request therefor, time being of the essence, failing which this Lease shall be deemed to be subordinate pursuant to the terms of this
<U>
	Article&nbsp;9
</U>
	.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Subject to Section&nbsp;9.1(a)&nbsp;above, if a Lessor or Mortgagee or any other person or entity shall succeed to the rights of Landlord under this Lease, whether through possession or foreclosure action or the delivery of a new lease or deed, then at the request of the successor landlord and upon such successor landlord&#146;s written agreement to accept Tenant&#146;s attornment and to recognize Tenant&#146;s interest under this Lease, Tenant shall be deemed to have attorned to and recognized such successor landlord as Landlord under this Lease.&#160; The provisions of this
<B>
	Section&nbsp;9.1
</B>
	are self-operative and require no further instruments to give effect hereto; provided, however, that Tenant shall promptly execute and deliver any instrument that such successor landlord may reasonably request (i)&nbsp;evidencing such attornment, (ii)&nbsp;setting forth the terms and conditions of Tenant&#146;s tenancy, and (iii)&nbsp;containing such other terms and conditions as may be reasonably required by such Mortgagee or Lessor, provided such terms and conditions do not increase the Rent, increase Tenant&#146;s other obligations or adversely affect Tenant&#146;s rights under this Lease, in each case beyond a de minimis extent and are in accordance with the Approved SNDA Form.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Upon such attornment this Lease shall continue in full force and effect as a direct lease between such successor landlord and Tenant upon all of the terms, conditions and covenants set forth in this Lease subject to the terms of the SNDA entered into by Tenant and such successor landlord (substantially as set forth in the Approved SNDA Form&nbsp;with reasonable modifications to reflect completion of Landlord&#146;s Work and other applicable changes (whether or not executed)).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(d)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Tenant shall from time to time within ten (10)&nbsp;Business Days of request from Landlord execute and deliver any documents or instruments that may be reasonably required by any Mortgagee or Lessor to confirm any subordination.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
	31
<A NAME="A2231003ZEX-10_17_HTM_1015-2-KU-07_PB_31_113852_7906">

<A NAME="eolPage235"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;9.2
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Mortgage or Superior Lease Defaults.&#160; Any Mortgagee may elect that this Lease shall have priority over the Mortgage and, upon notification to Tenant by such Mortgagee, this Lease shall be deemed to have priority over such Mortgage, regardless of the date of this Lease.&#160; In connection with any financing of the Real Property, Tenant shall consent to any reasonable modifications of this Lease requested by any lending institution, provided such modifications do not increase the Rent or increase the other obligations, or materially decrease Landlord&#146;s obligations, or adversely affect the rights, of Tenant under this Lease.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;9.3
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Tenant&#146;s Termination Right. As long as any Superior Lease or Mortgage exists, Tenant shall not seek to terminate this Lease by reason of any act or omission of Landlord until (a)&nbsp;Tenant shall have given notice of such act or omission to all Lessors and/or Mortgagees of which it has been provided actual notice, and (b)&nbsp;a reasonable period of time (not to exceed 120 days) shall have elapsed following the giving of notice of such default and the expiration of any applicable notice or grace periods (unless such act or omission is not capable of being remedied within a reasonable period of time), during which period such Lessors and/or Mortgagees shall have the right, but not the obligation, to remedy such act or omission and thereafter diligently proceed to so remedy such act or omission. If any Lessor or Mortgagee elects to remedy such act or omission of Landlord, Tenant shall not seek to terminate this Lease so long as such Lessor or Mortgagee is proceeding with reasonable diligence to effect such remedy (not to exceed 120 days). This Section&nbsp;9.3 does not apply to Tenant&#146;s ability to terminate this Lease in accordance with Sections 11.5, 11.6, and 12.1(d)&nbsp;or in connection with a termination permitted by Section&nbsp;10.1(b).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;9.4
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Provisions.&#160; The provisions of this
<B>
	Article&nbsp;9
</B>
	shall (a)&nbsp;inure to the benefit of Landlord, any future owner of the Building or the Real Property, Lessor or Mortgagee and any sublessor.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;9.5
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Future Condominium Declaration.&#160; This Lease and Tenant&#146;s rights hereunder are and will be subject and subordinate to any condominium declaration, by-laws and other instruments (collectively, the&#160; &#147;
<B>
	Declaration
</B>
	&#148;) which may be recorded in order to subject the Building to a condominium form of ownership pursuant to Article&nbsp;9-B of the New York Real Property Law or any successor Requirement, provided that the Declaration does not by its terms increase the Rent, materially increase Tenant&#146;s non-Rent obligations or materially and adversely affect Tenant&#146;s rights under this Lease.&#160; At Landlord&#146;s request, and subject to the foregoing proviso, Tenant will execute and deliver to Landlord an amendment of this Lease confirming such subordination and modifying this Lease to conform to such condominium regime and the condominium board delivers a subordination, non-disturbance and attornment agreement form reasonably satisfactory to Tenant
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;9.6
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Current Mortgagee SNDA.&#160; This Lease shall be binding on the parties upon full execution and delivery hereof but shall not be effective until delivery of an SNDA which meets the standard sets forth in Section&nbsp;9.1(a)&nbsp;in the Approved SNDA Form&nbsp;from Landlord&#146;s current Mortgagee.&#160; If Landlord shall fail to deliver to Tenant such an SNDA from its current Mortgagee within 60 days following the date on which this lease is fully-executed and delivered by Tenant and Landlord, Tenant shall have the right for 10 days after the expiration of such 60-day period to either waive the requirement of delivery of an SNDA or cancel this Lease by giving Landlord notice of such cancellation election (time being of the essence), whereupon this Lease shall become null and void as of the date which is 10 days after the giving of such notice of cancellation unless Landlord delivers such SNDA within 10 days after Tenant gave such cancellation notice, in which case Tenant&#146;s cancellation notice shall be void and this Lease shall continue in full force and effect. The failure by Tenant to expressly and timely cancel this Lease
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
	32
<A NAME="A2231003ZEX-10_17_HTM_1015-2-KU-07_PB_32_114009_3736">
</A>
