<A NAME="eolPage277"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Tenant is in default or for any sum which Landlord may expend by reason of Tenant&#146;s default hereunder.&#160; If Landlord applies any part of the Security Deposit so deposited, Tenant, upon demand, shall deposit with Landlord the amount so applied so that Landlord shall have the full Security Deposit on hand at all times during the Term.&#160; In addition to the foregoing, in the event of a termination of this Lease based upon the default of Tenant, or a rejection of this Lease pursuant to the provisions of the Federal Bankruptcy Code, Landlord shall have the right to retain the Security Deposit to cover the full amount of damages and other amounts due from Tenant to Landlord under this Lease.&#160; Any amounts so retained by Landlord shall, at Landlord&#146;s election, be applied first to any unpaid Rent and other charges that were due prior to the filing of the petition for protection under the Federal Bankruptcy Code.&#160; Tenant hereby covenants and agrees not to oppose, contest or otherwise interfere with any attempt by Landlord to draw down from said Letter of Credit (and/or Additional Letter of Credit) including, without limitation, by commencing an action seeking to enjoin or restrain Landlord from making such draw.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;27.4
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Transfer.&#160; In the event of a sale or foreclosure of the Building, Landlord shall transfer the Security Deposit to the vendee or Mortgagee and, provided the vendee or Mortgagee acknowledges the receipt of the Security Deposit in writing to Tenant, Landlord shall thereupon be released by Tenant from all liability for the return of such Security Deposit; and Tenant agrees to look to the new Landlord solely for the return of said Security Deposit, and it is agreed that the provisions hereof shall apply to every transfer or assignment made of the Security Deposit to a new Landlord.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;27.5
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Encumbrance.&#160; Tenant covenants that it will not assign or encumber, or attempt to assign or encumber, the Letter of Credit deposited hereunder as security, and that neither Landlord nor its successors or assigns shall be bound by any such assignment, encumbrance, attempted assignment, or attempted encumbrance.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;27.6
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	No Waiver.&#160; The use of security, as provided in this Article, shall not be deemed or construed as a waiver of Tenant&#146;s default or as a waiver of any other rights and remedies to which Landlord may be entitled under the provisions of this Lease by reason of such default, it being intended that Landlord&#146;s rights to use the whole or any part of the security shall be in addition to but not in limitation of any such other rights and remedies; and Landlord may exercise any of such other rights and remedies independent of or in conjunction with its rights under this Article.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;27.7
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Return of Letter of Credit.&#160; Within sixty (60) days after the Expiration Date and the vacation of the Premises by Tenant and delivery of the Premises to landlord in the condition required hereunder, the Letter of Credit or such part thereof that has not been applied to cure any defaults, beyond applicable and notice and cure periods, shall be returned to Tenant.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;27.8
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Extension Option.&#160; If Tenant exercises its option to extend the Term pursuant to
<B>
	Article&nbsp;31
</B>
	of this Lease then, not later than 60 days prior to the commencement of the Renewal Term, Tenant shall deliver to Landlord a new Letter of Credit or certificate of renewal or extension evidencing that such new Letter of Credit be for a term of one (1)&nbsp;year, subject to automatic one (1)&nbsp;year extensions so that the Letter of Credit is in effect until a date which is at least sixty (60) days after the scheduled Expiration Date (taking into consideration any then exercised extension option), as same may be extended.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Reduction.&#160; Provided no monetary defaults in payment of either (x)&nbsp;Fixed Rent or (y)&nbsp;additional rent in excess of $25,000, in either case occurred more than three times in any 12 month period, and no Event of Default then exists, then, provided that Tenant complies

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	with the provisions of this
<B>
	Section&nbsp;27.9
</B>
	, (i)&nbsp;on the third (3
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	rd
</FONT>
	) anniversary of the Rent Commencement Date, the Security Deposit shall be reduced to $3,110,625.00, and (ii)&nbsp;provided the Security Deposit shall have previously been reduced pursuant to the preceding clause (i), on the fifth (5
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	th
</FONT>
	) anniversary of the Rent Commencement Date the Security Deposit shall be further reduced to $2,504,250.00. The Security Deposit shall be reduced as follows: (A)&nbsp;if the Security Deposit is in the form of cash, Landlord shall, within 10 Business Days following notice by Tenant to Landlord that Tenant is entitled to reduce the Security Deposit pursuant to this
<B>
	Section&nbsp;27.9
</B>
	, deliver to Tenant the amount by which the Security Deposit is reduced, or (B)&nbsp;if the Security Deposit is in the form of a Letter of Credit, Tenant shall deliver to Landlord a consent to an amendment to the Letter of Credit (which amendment must be reasonably acceptable to Landlord in all respects), reducing the amount of the Letter of Credit by the amount of the permitted reduction, and Landlord shall execute such consent and such other documents as are reasonably necessary to reduce the amount of the Letter of Credit in accordance with the terms hereof. If Tenant delivers to Landlord an amendment to the Letter of Credit in accordance with the terms hereof, Landlord shall, within 10 Business Days after delivery of such consent, either (1)&nbsp;provide its reasonable objections to such amendment or (2)&nbsp;execute such consent in accordance with the terms hereof.

<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ARTICLE&nbsp;28
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	OFAC
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Neither a Sanctioned Person (as hereinafter defined) nor Sanctioned Entity (as hereinafter defined) will benefit directly or indirectly through this Lease. Landlord and Tenant each (as to itself) hereby respectively covenant and warrant that:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	it is not directly or indirectly controlled by a Sanctioned Entity or a Sanctioned Person.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	it, nor any of its subsidiaries (a)&nbsp;is a Sanctioned Person, (b)&nbsp;has more than an insubstantial portion of its assets located in Sanctioned Entities, or (iii)&nbsp;derives more than an insubstantial portion of its operating income from investments in, or transactions with, Sanctioned Persons or Sanctioned Entities.&#160; OFAC means The Office of Foreign Assets Control of the U.S. Department of the Treasury (&#147;
<B>
	OFAC
</B>
	&#148;).&#160; &#147;Sanctioned Entity&#148; means: (a)&nbsp;an agency of the government of; (b)&nbsp;an organization directly or indirectly controlled by; or (c)&nbsp;a person resident in a country that is subject to a country sanctions program administered and enforced by OFAC described or referenced at OFAC&#146;s website http://www.ustreas.gov/offices/enforcement/ofac/ or as otherwise published from time to time.&#160; &#147;Sanctioned Person&#148; means a person named on the list of Specially Designated Nationals maintained by OFAC available at or through OFAC&#146;s website http://www.ustreas.gov/offices/enforcement/ofac/ or as otherwise published from time to time.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ARTICLE&nbsp;29
<BR>
	ICAP
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;29.1
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Landlord may, at Landlord&#146;s sole cost and expense, prepare and submit its application for the granting of the New York State Tax Requirement and the Administrative Code of the City of New York, the Industrial and Commercial Abatement Program (&#147;
<B>
	ICAP
</B>
	&#148;) tax benefits.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<A NAME="eolPage279"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	To the extent required by Landlord (with the parties hereby acknowledging that most if not all of the abatement attributable to the ICAP abatement program for the Building will be derived from the applicable work to be performed to the Building), Tenant shall, reasonably&#160; cooperate with Landlord, at no material cost (unless Landlord agrees to pay such cost) in good faith in connection with the preparation of the application for the ICAP abatement, including supplying all available information and documentation required of Tenant and/or in connection with Tenant work.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Once the ICAP application has been submitted by Landlord, Landlord shall use all diligent efforts to pursue such application process.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Once the ICAP Abatement shall have been obtained, and thereafter during the Term, Tenant and Landlord shall, in a diligent and timely manner, comply with all of their respective requirements with respect to maintaining and preserving the ICAP Abatement including to duly and timely file all necessary reports, statements and schedules required to maintain the ICAP abatement in full force and effect.&#160; Nothing contained in this
<B>
	Article&nbsp;29
</B>
	shall obligate Tenant to take any action or file any report, statement or schedule with respect to the Work or its employees.&#160; Additionally, nothing contained in this
<B>
	Article&nbsp;29
</B>
	shall obligate Tenant to take any action or incur any expense beyond what is required of Tenant under and pursuant to the ICAP program so as to allow Landlord to provide required access to the Premises and submit required data and information known only to Tenant in order for Landlord to preserve and maintain the ICAP benefits.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(d)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Throughout the term of the ICAP abatement neither Landlord nor Tenant shall knowingly engage in any act or conduct which will jeopardize or void the abatement, subject to circumstances outside their control.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(e)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	If and to the extent required for purposes of eligibility for the ICAP abatement, Landlord shall perform Landlord&#146;s Premises Work and Landlord&#146;s Expansion Premises Work and Tenant shall perform all Alterations in material compliance with any ICAP eligibility requirements (including, if and to the extent required for eligibility in connection with the ICAP abatement, any Minority and Women-Owned Business Enterprise firm requirements).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this
<B>
	Article&nbsp;29
</B>
	, in the event that Landlord and Tenant are unable to obtain the ICAP abatement as provided herein, this Lease shall nevertheless remain in full force and effect.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;29.2
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	It is further understood and agreed that (in order to enable Landlord to comply with certain requirements of the ICAP abatement):
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Tenant (and/or its contractors and subcontractors) agrees to report to Landlord the nature of its business, the number of workers permanently engaged in employment in the Premises, the nature of each worker&#146;s employment (i.e., job classification or job title) and the New York City residency of each worker (and the names and addresses of such residents if required by New York City for verification) and Tenant will require that a clause similar to this be contained in any sublease, passing to the benefit of Tenant and of Landlord, if any sublease of all or a portion of the Premises is made;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Tenant (and/or its contractors and subcontractors) shall reasonably&#160; cooperate with Landlord, and Tenant (and/or its contractors and subcontractors) will supply such information and comply with such reporting requirements as Landlord advises Tenant are
</P>

	reasonably necessary to comply with the ICAP Abatement to the extent relating to the Premises, including, but not limited to:&#160; (a)&nbsp;such information concerning subleases (including a rent roll with respect thereto); and (b)&nbsp;the filing of employment reports and other such forms with the Division of Labor Services.&#160; The parties will assist each other in connection with maintaining eligibility under the ICAP Abatement; and

To the extent required, all Alterations must be done in strict compliance with ICAP and the filing of employment reports and other such forms with the Division of Labor Services.&#160; The parties will assist each other in connection with maintaining eligibility under ICAP.

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ARTICLE&nbsp;30
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	MUNICIPAL AND TAX INCENTIVES
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Landlord shall, at no cost, expense, liability or adverse effect on Landlord, the Building and/or other tenants, cooperate with Tenant in obtaining any municipal incentives, LEED certifications or tax benefits, including but not limited to REAP benefits, in connection with this Lease and the Premises for which Tenant may qualify or seek to qualify provided that such municipal and tax incentives shall have no adverse impact upon Landlord, the Premises, the Building and/or the Dumbo Heights Campus.&#160; Tenant hereby agrees, at Tenant&#146;s expense, to comply with Landlord&#146;s reasonable requirements in connection with performing work and/or making installations that are compatible with Landlord&#146;s LEED (or other comparable) standards for the Building.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ARTICLE&nbsp;31
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	RENEWAL TERM
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;31.1
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Renewal Term.&#160; Tenant shall have the right to renew the Term for all of the Premises only for one (1)&nbsp;renewal term of 5 (five) years (the &#147;
<B>
	Renewal Term
</B>
	&#148;) commencing on the day after the expiration of the initial Term (the &#147;
<B>
	Renewal Term Commencement Date
</B>
	&#148;) and ending on the day last day of the calendar month immediately preceding the fifth anniversary of the Renewal Term Commencement Date, unless the Renewal Term shall sooner terminate pursuant to any of the terms of this Lease or otherwise.&#160; The Renewal Term shall commence only if (a)&nbsp;Tenant notifies Landlord (the &#147;
<B>
	Exercise Notice
</B>
	&#148;) of Tenant&#146;s exercise of such renewal right not later than fifteen (15) months prior to the Expiration Date, (b)&nbsp;at the time of the exercise of such right and immediately prior to the Renewal Term Commencement Date, no Event of Default shall have occurred and be continuing hereunder, and (c)&nbsp;Tenant named herein and/or an assignee permitted under
<B>
	Section&nbsp;13.8(a)
</B>
	&nbsp;without Landlord&#146;s consent thereof
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
	82
<A NAME="A2231003ZEX-10_17_HTM_1015-2-KU-17_PB_82_114230_8627">
</A>

<!-- ZEQ.=1,SEQ=85,EFW="2231003",CP="2U, INC.",DN="3",CHK=128700,FOLIO='82',FILE="DISK131:[17ZAA2.17ZAA11502]1015-2-KU-17_ZAA11502.CHC",USER="HYUNG",CD='FEB 23 11:44 2017' -->
<A NAME="eolPage281"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	occupy at least two full contiguous floors in the Building (the &#147;
<B>
	Occupancy Threshold
</B>
	&#148;) at the time the Exercise Notice is given.&#160; Time is of the essence with respect to the giving of the Exercise Notice.&#160; The Renewal Term shall be upon all of the agreements, terms, covenants and conditions of this Lease, except that (x)&nbsp;the Fixed Rent shall be determined as provided in
<B>
	Section&nbsp;31.2
</B>
	, (y)&nbsp;Tenant shall have no further right to renew the Term,&#160; and (z)&nbsp;the Base Tax Year shall be the Tax Year commencing on the July&nbsp;1st of the calendar year in which the Renewal Term Commencement Date occurs and (z)&nbsp;the Base Expense Year shall be the calendar year in which the Renewal term Commencement Date occurs.&#160; Upon the commencement of the Renewal Term, (1)&nbsp;the Renewal Term shall be added to and become part of the Term, (2)&nbsp;any reference to &#147;this Lease&#148;, to the &#147;Term&#148;, the &#147;term of this Lease&#148; or any similar expression shall be deemed to include the Renewal Term, and (3)&nbsp;the expiration of the Renewal Term shall become the Expiration Date. Any termination, cancellation or surrender of the entire interest of Tenant under this Lease at any time during the Term shall terminate any right of renewal of Tenant hereunder.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;31.2
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Renewal Term Rent.&#160; The annual Fixed Rent payable during the Renewal Term shall be equal to the greater of (a)&nbsp;the annual Fair Market Value (as hereinafter defined) as of the Renewal Term Commencement Date and (b)&nbsp;the annual Fixed Rent then in effect at the expiration of the initial term of this Lease.&#160; &#147;
<B>
	Fair Market Value
</B>
	&#148; shall mean the fair market annual rental value of the Premises as of the Renewal Term Commencement Date for a term equal to the Renewal Term, based on comparable space in the Building, or on comparable space in Comparable Buildings, including all of Landlord&#146;s services provided for in this Lease, and with (i)&nbsp;the Premises considered as vacant, and in &#147;as is&#148; condition existing on the Renewal Term Commencement Date, and (ii)&nbsp;the Base Tax Year being the Tax Year commencing on the July&nbsp;1st of the calendar year in which the Renewal Term Commencement Date occurs.&#160; The calculation of Fair Market Value shall also be adjusted to take into account all other relevant factors.&#160; Landlord shall advise Tenant (the &#147;
<B>
	Rent Notice
</B>
	&#148;) of Landlord&#146;s determination of Fair Market Value prior to the Renewal Term Commencement Date. If Tenant disputes Landlord&#146;s determination of Fair Market Value, Tenant shall provide its determination of Fair Market Value within 10 days after Landlord delivers the Rent Notice and in such event the dispute shall be resolved by arbitration as provided in
<B>
	Section&nbsp;31.3
</B>
	. If the Fixed Rent payable during the Renewal Term is not determined prior to the Renewal Term Commencement Date, Tenant shall pay Fixed Rent in an amount equal to the Fair Market Value for the Premises as determined by Landlord (the &#147;
<B>
	Interim Rent
</B>
	&#148;).&#160; Upon final determination of the Fixed Rent for the Renewal Term, Tenant shall commence paying such Fixed Rent as so determined, and within 10 days after such determination Tenant shall pay any deficiency in prior payments of Fixed Rent or, if the Fixed Rent as so determined shall be less than the Interim Rent, Tenant shall be entitled to a credit against the next succeeding installments of Fixed Rent in an amount equal to the difference between each installment of Interim Rent and the Fixed Rent as so determined which should have been paid for such installment until the total amount of the over payment has been recouped.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;31.3
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Arbitration.&#160; If Tenant timely disputes Landlord&#146;s determination of Fair Market Value pursuant to
<B>
	Section&nbsp;31.2
</B>
	, Tenant shall give notice to Landlord of such dispute within 10 Business Days after delivery of the Rent Notice (provided a failure to so timely dispute shall be deemed acceptance of Landlord&#146;s determination of Fair Market Value), and such dispute shall be determined by arbitration in accordance with the then prevailing Expedited Procedures of the Arbitration Rules&nbsp;for the Real Estate Industry of the American Arbitration Association or its successor for arbitration of commercial disputes, except that the rules&nbsp;shall be modified as follows:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
	83
<A NAME="A2231003ZEX-10_17_HTM_1015-2-KU-17_PB_83_114251_7906">
</A>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="100%" NOSHADE ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="COLOR:#010101;">

<!-- ZEQ.=1,SEQ=86,EFW="2231003",CP="2U, INC.",DN="3",CHK=394424,FOLIO='83',FILE="DISK131:[17ZAA2.17ZAA11502]1015-2-KU-17_ZAA11502.CHC",USER="HYUNG",CD='FEB 23 11:44 2017' -->
<A NAME="eolPage282"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	In its demand for arbitration Tenant shall specify the name and address of the person to act as the arbitrator on Tenant&#146;s behalf.&#160; The arbitrator shall be a real estate broker with at least 10 years full-time commercial brokerage experience who is familiar with the fair market value of first-class office space in the Borough of Brooklyn, City of New York, New York. Failure on the part of Tenant to make the timely and proper demand for such arbitration shall constitute a waiver of the right thereto and the Fixed Rent shall be as set forth in the Rent Notice.&#160; Within 10 Business Days after the service of the demand for arbitration, Landlord shall give notice to Tenant specifying the name and address of the person designated by Landlord to act as arbitrator on its behalf, which arbitrator shall be similarly qualified.&#160; If Landlord fails to notify Tenant of the appointment of its arbitrator within such 10 Business Day period, and such failure continues for 5 Business Days after Tenant delivers a second notice to Landlord,&#160; then the arbitrator appointed by Tenant shall be the arbitrator to determine the Fair Market Value for the Premises.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	If two arbitrators are chosen pursuant to Section&nbsp;31.3(a), the arbitrators so chosen shall meet within 10 Business Days after the second arbitrator is appointed and shall seek to reach agreement on Fair Market Value. If within 20 Business Days after the second arbitrator is appointed the two arbitrators are unable to reach agreement on Fair Market Value then the two arbitrators shall appoint a third arbitrator, who shall be a competent and impartial person with qualifications similar to those required of the first two arbitrators pursuant to Section&nbsp;31.3(a).&#160; If they are unable to agree upon such appointment within 5 Business Days after expiration of such 20 Business Day period, the third arbitrator shall be selected by the parties themselves.&#160; If the parties do not agree on the third arbitrator within 5 Business Days after expiration of the foregoing 5 Business Day period, then either party, on behalf of both, may request appointment of such a qualified person by the then president of the Real Estate Board of New York.&#160; The third arbitrator shall decide the dispute, if it has not been previously resolved, by following the procedures set forth in Section&nbsp;31.3(c).&#160; Each party shall pay the fees and expenses of its respective arbitrator and both shall share the fees and expenses of the third arbitrator.&#160; Attorneys&#146; fees and expenses of counsel and of witnesses for the respective parties shall be paid by the respective party engaging such counsel or calling such witnesses.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Fair Market Value shall be fixed by the third arbitrator in accordance with the following procedures.&#160; Concurrently with the appointment of the third arbitrator, each of the arbitrators selected by the parties shall state, in writing, his or her determination of the Fair Market Value supported by the reasons therefor. &#160;The third arbitrator shall have the right to consult experts and competent authorities for factual information or evidence pertaining to a determination of Fair Market Value, but any such determination shall be made in the presence of both parties with full right on their part to cross-examine. The third arbitrator shall conduct such hearings and investigations as he or she deem appropriate and shall, within 30 days after being appointed, select which of the two proposed determinations most closely approximates his or her determination of Fair Market Value.&#160; The third arbitrator shall have no right to propose a middle ground or any modification of either of the two proposed determinations.&#160; The determination he or she chooses as that most closely approximating his or her determination of the Fair Market Value shall constitute the decision of the third arbitrator and shall be final and binding upon the parties.&#160; The third arbitrator shall render the decision in writing with counterpart copies to each party. The third arbitrator shall have no power to add to or modify the provisions of this Lease. Promptly following receipt of the third arbitrator&#146;s decision, the parties shall enter into an amendment to this Lease evidencing the extension of the Term for the Renewal Term and confirming the Fixed Rent for the Renewal Term, but the failure of the parties to do so shall not affect the effectiveness of the third arbitrator&#146;s determination.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
	84
<A NAME="A2231003ZEX-10_17_HTM_1015-2-KU-17_PB_84_114306_3736">
</A>

<A NAME="eolPage283"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(d)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	In the event of a failure, refusal or inability of any arbitrator to act, his or her successor shall be appointed by him or her, but in the case of the third arbitrator, his or her successor shall be appointed in the same manner as that set forth herein with respect to the appointment of the original third arbitrator.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ARTICLE&nbsp;32
<BR>
	LANDLORD TAKE-OVER OBLIGATIONS
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;32.1
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Tenant represents and warrants to Landlord:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Tenant is now the lessee under a certain Sublease, dated as of November&nbsp;11, 2009 between Chelsea Piers L.P., as sublessor (&#147;
<B>
	Original Guarantor Lessor
</B>
	&#148;) and 2tor,&nbsp;Inc. (Guarantor&#146;s previous name), as sublessee (&#147;
<B>
	Guarantor
</B>
	&#148;), for 8,000 rsf at Pier 59 &#151; level 2 (the &#147;
<B>
	Original Sublease
</B>
	&#148; and such premises, the &#147;
<B>
	Pier 59 Premises
</B>
	&#148;), as amended by (i)&nbsp;a First Amendment to Sublease, dated as of July&nbsp;26, 2011, between Original Guarantor&#146;s Lessor&#146;s successor, Waterfront Services,&nbsp;Inc. (&#147;
<B>
	Guarantor&#146;s Present Lessor
</B>
	&#148;) and Guarantor, which. among other changes, added approximately 8,402 rsf in Pier 60 (the &#147;
<B>
	Pier 60 Premises
</B>
	&#148;), (ii)&nbsp;a Second Amendment to Sublease, dated September&nbsp;19, 2013, between Guarantor&#146;s Present Lessor and Guarantor, as sublessee, which among other changes, added 2,632 rsf in Pier 62 identified as Suite&nbsp;203 (the &#147;
<B>
	Suite&nbsp;203 Premises
</B>
	&#148;), (iii)&nbsp;a Third Amendment to Sublease, dated December&nbsp;31, 2014, between Guarantor&#146;s Present Lessor and Guarantor, which, among other changes, added 1,974 rsf in Pier 62, identified as M100 (the &#147;
<B>
	M100 Premises
</B>
	&#148; and together with the Pier 59 Premises, the Pier 60 Premises and the Suite&nbsp;203 Premises, the &#147;
<B>
	Guarantor&#146;s Present Space
</B>
	&#148;) and (iv)&nbsp;a Fourth Amendment to Sublease, dated September&nbsp;30, 2016, which among other changes, extended the term for the Pier 59 Premises from December&nbsp;31, 2016 to December&nbsp;31, 2017 (as so amended, &#147;
<B>
	Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement
</B>
	&#148;). All annual fixed rent and rental payable by Guarantor under Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement (which agreement shall not be modified without Landlord&#146;s consent) on account of utility expenses, operating expenses and taxes, without taking into account holdover penalty, interest or late charges unless attributable to Landlord&#146;s wrongful acts (&#147;
<B>
	Escalation Payments
</B>
	&#148;) are collectively referred to herein as the &#147;
<B>
	Takeover Rent
</B>
	&#148;;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Guarantor has entered into the following sub-subleases of the Guarantor&#146;s Present Space: Sublease dated December&nbsp;16, 2011 between Guarantor, as sub-sublessor, and Noodle Education,&nbsp;Inc with respect to all of the Pier 59 Premises (the &#147;
<B>
	Noodle Sub-sublease
</B>
	&#148;) which sub-sublease expires on December&nbsp;31, 2016;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	With the exception of Guarantor&#146;s sublease of the Pier 59 Premises, Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement expires December&nbsp;31, 2019;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(d)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement has not been modified or supplemented except as described above;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">

	(e)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">

	(f)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

	Except for the Noodle Sub-sublease, there are no subleases, licenses or other occupancy agreements or any other agreement except Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement pertaining to Tenant leasing or occupancy of Guarantor&#146;s Present Space and no other party occupies or has a right to occupy or use Guarantor&#146;s Present Space.
</P>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">

	Section&nbsp;32.2
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Landlord represents and warrants to Tenant that:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Landlord has reviewed Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;32.3
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Tenant desires to relocate its business to the Premises; however, because Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement does not expire prior to the Commencement Date of this Lease, Landlord has agreed to reimburse Tenant for the Takeover Rent in an aggregate amount up to (but not exceeding) $1,500,000 (the &#147;
<B>
	Takeover Amount
</B>
	&#148;), subject to and in accordance with the terms of this Article&nbsp;32.&#160; For the avoidance of doubt, in no event shall Landlord be responsible to reimburse Tenant for the Takeover Rent in an aggregate amount which exceeds $1,500,000. Notwithstanding the foregoing, if the Commencement Date does not occur on or prior to August&nbsp;15, 2017, then for each day after such date until the Commencement Date occurs, all references to $1,500,000 in this Section&nbsp;shall be reduced by $1,728.11 for each day thereafter until the Commencement Date occurs.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">

	Section&nbsp;32.4
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Commencing as of the date that Guarantor and its affiliates have vacated Guarantor&#146;s Present Space and Tenant has commenced occupancy of the Premises for the normal conduct of its business (the &#147;
<B>
	Takeover Date
</B>
	&#148;):
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Guarantor shall not perform any alterations or other work in Guarantor&#146;s Present Space nor enter into any agreements to provide any party with any rights to such space, without in any event, Landlord&#146;s consent (not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed);
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Guarantor shall not, without Landlord&#146;s consent (not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed), at any time hereafter commit or suffer, any act, deed, matter or thing whatsoever whereby Guarantor&#146;s Present Space or any part thereof shall at any time hereafter in any way be impeached, charged, affected, or encumbered by Guarantor or Tenant;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Guarantor shall submit to Landlord, promptly after receipt by Guarantor, true copies of any notices, bills, invoices, statements or other documents received by Guarantor from and after the date hereof in connection with Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement and/or Tenant&#146;s occupancy in Guarantor&#146;s Present Space;
</P>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">

	(d)
</FONT>

</FONT>
	Subject to the provisions of this Article&nbsp;32, Landlord agrees to provide Guarantor with the monthly installment of Takeover Rent that Guarantor is required to pay to Guarantor&#146;s Present Lessor with respect to the period commencing on the first day of the calendar month following the Takeover Date and ending on&#160; the date of the expiration of the term of Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement (or sooner termination thereof provided such

<!-- ZEQ.=1,SEQ=89,EFW="2231003",CP="2U, INC.",DN="3",CHK=635841,FOLIO='86',FILE="DISK131:[17ZAA2.17ZAA11502]1015-2-KU-17_ZAA11502.CHC",USER="HYUNG",CD='FEB 23 11:44 2017' -->
<A NAME="eolPage285"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	termination includes a release of Guarantor from any Takeover Rent obligations under Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement accruing after such termination date or the termination of this Lease, whichever occurs first. Promptly following Guarantor&#146;s receipt of the same, Guarantor shall provide Landlord with a copy of the rent bill for the month preceding the Takeover Date and Landlord shall include in each monthly installment of the Takeover Rent an amount on account of Escalation Payments based on the amounts so shown on such rent bill, subject to the terms of this Article&nbsp;32. Each monthly installment of the Takeover Rent if applicable, shall at Guarantor&#146;s option, either be paid to Guarantor monthly, in advance, on or before the twenty-fifth (25th) day of the month immediately preceding the month for which such sums are due or in the form of a credit against Fixed Rent payable under this Lease, except that if the Takeover Date occurs towards the end of the calendar month, then the payment of Takeover Rent by Landlord on account of the first month following the Takeover Date shall be paid by Landlord to Guarantor within ten (10)&nbsp;business days of the Takeover Date. In furtherance of the foregoing, the Takeover Rent shall not include amounts billed to Guarantor after the Takeover Date that relate in any manner to the period prior to the Takeover Date.&#160; In the event that there shall be an abatement of fixed rent and/or Escalation Payments under Tenant&#146;s Present Letting Agreement, the Takeover Amount shall be equitably reduced to reflect such abatement (provided that the term of the Tenant&#146;s Present Letting Agreement is not automatically extended as the result of such abatement).&#160; No payment or credit shall be required by Landlord for periods during which an Event of Default exists; provided that upon Tenant&#146;s cure of any such defaults, such payments or credits shall be immediately paid or credited to Guarantor. Landlord shall not be responsible for any additional rent, costs or other charges or payments attributable to Tenant&#146;s default, negligence, or misconduct under Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement unless caused by Landlord&#146;s Subtenants (as hereinafter defined).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;32.5
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	In the event that the monthly rental amounts Guarantor must pay to Guarantor&#146;s Present Lessor shall be modified on account of changes in the Escalation Payments, Guarantor shall advise Landlord and deliver to Landlord a copy of the rent bill from Guarantor&#146;s Present Lessor evidencing such modification and the monthly installment of Takeover Rent to be paid by Landlord shall be adjusted to reflect such modification. Tenant acknowledges that Landlord may desire to cause an audit of operating expenses for escalation years occurring any time after the Takeover Date to the extent such audits are permitted by the Tenant&#146;s Present Letting Agreement.&#160; Tenant shall promptly provide Landlord with a copy of any operating expense statement provided to Tenant after its receipt thereof and, at Landlord&#146;s request, shall exercise its right to cause an audit of the same.&#160; Any audit shall be performed by personnel selected by Landlord at Landlord&#146;s sole cost and expense (but subject to the limitations set forth in Tenant&#146;s Present Letting Agreement).&#160; Any refund of Escalation Payments on account of the period preceding the first calendar month following the Takeover Date shall be for the benefit of Guarantor and any refunds on account of the period commencing with such month following the Takeover Date shall be for the benefit of Landlord.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;32.6
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	During the period after the Takeover Date, Guarantor agrees, upon request of Landlord, (i)&nbsp;to enter into one or more agreements with Guarantor&#146;s Present Lessor surrendering all or any portions of Guarantor&#146;s Present Space (including pursuant to Guarantor&#146;s Present Lessor&#146;s recapture rights), and/or (ii)&nbsp;subject to the approval of Guarantor&#146;s Present Lessor, to assign its interest in and to Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement to any assignee or assignees designated by Landlord, and/or (iii)&nbsp;subject to the approval of Guarantor&#146;s Present Lessor, and the terms of Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement, enter into one or more subleases affecting all or any portions of Guarantor&#146;s Present Space with any sublessee or sublessees designated by Landlord (&#147;
<B>
	Landlord Subtenants
</B>
	&#148;) at any rental and upon any other
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
	87
<A NAME="A2231003ZEX-10_17_HTM_1015-2-KU-17_PB_87_114400_563">
</A>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="100%" NOSHADE ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="COLOR:#010101;">
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	terms which Landlord may designate in said request, provided said terms do not violate any of the provisions of Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement and provided that Guarantor&#146;s obligations under Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement shall not be increased without Guarantor&#146;s consent. Any payments to Guarantor&#146;s Present Lessor in connection with any of the aforesaid agreements and/or other transactions costs shall be borne by Landlord and not credited against the Takeover Amount (and Landlord agrees to indemnify Tenant and Guarantor in connection with such payments), but such amounts shall be deemed to be Transaction Costs (as hereinafter defined). Guarantor further agrees (i)&nbsp;to reasonably cooperate with Landlord to bring about any such proposed surrender agreement, assignment or sublease and obtain Guarantor&#146;s Present Lessor&#146;s agreement or consent thereto, including without limitation by delivering a notice to commence the recapture process in the Present Letting Agreement upon Landlord&#146;s request provided that no such notice shall be delivered prior to the Takeover Date, and (ii)&nbsp;to timely deliver or cause to be delivered, at any time subsequent to the Takeover Date, the premises affected by any such surrender agreement, assignment or sublease to Guarantor&#146;s Present Lessor in the condition required by the surrender agreement or the Present Letting Agreement. Once consummated, Guarantor shall not amend any such transaction documents without Landlord&#146;s consent. Landlord shall indemnify, defend and hold Guarantor harmless from and against any direct out-of-pocket loss, cost and expenses, including reasonable attorneys&#146; fees and disbursements (but not holdover costs or consequential damages payable to Guarantor&#146;s Present Lessor except as expressly provided below) arising out of a breach of or default under Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement or any damage to the Guarantor&#146;s Present Space solely caused by or attributable to any Landlord&#146;s Subtenant for failure to comply with the terms of its occupancy agreement with Tenant.&#160; Landlord does not need to obtain Guarantor&#146;s consent to any proposed Landlord&#146;s Subtenant, provided that (i)&nbsp;if Landlord does not obtain Guarantor&#146;s consent (or Guarantor is asked by Landlord to consent and Guarantor refuses to consent), Landlord will retain all Sublease Profits (as hereinafter defined), if any, and bear all holdover costs (including consequential damages) incurred by Guarantor under the Present Letting Agreement in connection with such Landlord&#146;s Subtenant holdover after the expiration of the applicable term and (ii)&nbsp;if Landlord does obtain Guarantor&#146;s consent, Landlord and Guarantor will share the Sublease Profits (50/50) and each bear 50% of the holdover costs (including consequential damages) incurred in connection with such Landlord&#146;s Subtenant&#146;s holdover.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;32.7
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	In the event that a surrender of all Guarantor&#146;s Present Space shall be consummated, Landlord shall have no further obligation to make payments of the Takeover Amount and in the event that a partial surrender is effectuated the Takeover Amount shall be equitably reduced to reflect such surrender taking into account the proportion of the Takeover Rent which is no longer payable.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	In the event that Tenant shall receive any consideration as a result of an early termination of Tenant&#146;s Present Letting Agreement in excess of the outstanding balance of the Takeover Amount, upon Tenant&#146;s actual receipt thereof, Tenant shall promptly reimburse Landlord for any Present Letting Agreement Transaction Costs (as hereinafter defined) up to the then outstanding and unreimbursed Present Letting Agreement Transaction Costs, and any excess consideration may be retained by Tenant.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	In the event that any Landlord&#146;s Subleases shall be consummated, all fixed and escalation rent and utility payments payable by the subtenants thereunder shall be applied by Guarantor to reduce the balance of the Takeover Amount payable by Landlord to
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">

<A NAME="eolPage286"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Tenant. Upon the balance of the Takeover Amount being reduced to zero, then within five (5)&nbsp;business days of Guarantor&#146;s receipt of any monthly rental payments in excess of the Takeover Rent and other amounts then payable by Guarantor to Guarantor&#146;s Present Lessor under Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement (including any profit sharing if required by Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement) (such amount, &#147;
<B>
	Guarantor&#146;s Monthly Rent Obligation
</B>
	&#148; and such funds in excess thereof, the &#147;
<B>
	Excess Monthly Sublease Rent
</B>
	&#148;), (i)&nbsp;Guarantor shall remit such Excess Monthly Sublease Rent on a monthly basis until Landlord has received a full reimbursement for all Present Letting Agreement Transaction Costs actually incurred by Landlord.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(d)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Once Landlord has received a full reimbursement of any Present Letting Agreement Transaction Costs actually incurred by Landlord, all funds in excess thereof&#160; (&#147;
<B>
	Sublease Profits
</B>
	&#148;) shall be payable as follows: (i)&nbsp;if Guarantor has previously approved such Landlord&#146;s Sublease, Guarantor and Landlord shall share such Sublease Profits equally (50/50) and (ii)&nbsp;if Guarantor has not previously approved such Landlord&#146;s Sublease, Landlord shall retain all such Sublease Profits
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(e)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	As aforesaid, Guarantor shall not cancel, amend or supplement any sublease without Landlord&#146;s consent and Guarantor also shall not waive any right to receive any payment from any subtenant. Guarantor shall use reasonable efforts to enforce the provisions of any such sublease(s)&nbsp;and upon Landlord&#146;s request shall take such actions or institute proceedings and diligently pursue the same as directed by Landlord to enforce the provisions of such sublease(s)&nbsp;and to enforce the provisions of Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement, using Landlord&#146;s counsel or, at Landlord&#146;s election, using Guarantor&#146;s counsel at Landlord&#146;s reasonable cost and expense (which reasonable costs and expenses shall either be billed directly to Landlord or shall be reimbursed by Landlord to Guarantor). At Landlord&#146;s option and to the extent permissible, Guarantor shall assign to Landlord its right to institute, at Landlord&#146;s sole cost and expense, proceedings against such subtenant(s)&nbsp;to enforce the provisions of such sublease(s)&nbsp;and/or regain possession of the space affected by such sublease(s).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(f)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	As used herein, the term &#147;
<B>
	Present Letting Agreement Transaction Costs
</B>
	&#148; shall mean any and all reasonable third party costs related to a sublease, assignment, or early termination of Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement incurred by Landlord, including, without limitation, (i)&nbsp;any tenant improvement work allowance or any construction costs paid or to be paid in connection with such transaction, (ii)&nbsp;in the case of any sublease, any actual costs incurred in separately demising the sublet space, (iii)&nbsp;any&#160; brokerage payment due to a broker in connection with an assignment, sublease, or early termination of the Present Letting Agreement (which payment shall be paid by Landlord), and (v)&nbsp;any termination fees paid to Guarantor&#146;s Present Lessor. Provided Present Letting Agreement Transaction Costs shall not include any indemnification paid or payable to Guarantor or Tenant in connection with Landlord&#146;s Subleases.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;32.8
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	In the event that Landlord shall fail to timely pay or reimburse Guarantor for any Takeover Rent or any other amounts payable or reimbursable by Landlord to Guarantor pursuant to this Article&nbsp;32 (and not in reasonably in dispute by Landlord) and such failure continues for thirty (30) days after Guarantor&#146;s notice thereof to Landlord and Guarantor&#146;s payment of such outstanding amounts to Guarantor&#146;s Present Lessor, Tenant shall have the right, without further notice, so offset such amounts from any Rent payable by Tenant hereunder, provided no Event of Default then exists.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
