<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;32.9
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Guarantor and Tenant shall not cause a default under the Guarantor&#146;s Present Letting Agreement.&#160; In the event of any such default caused by Tenant or Guarantor, Tenant shall indemnify Landlord and hold Landlord harmless from and against any loss or liability (including, but not limited to, reasonable attorney&#146;s fees and expenses) which Landlord may pay or incur by reason of such default.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ARTICLE&nbsp;33
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	EXPANSION PREMISES
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;33.1
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Commencing on the Expansion Premises Commencement Date and ending on the Expiration Date, Landlord shall lease to Tenant, and Tenant shall hire from Landlord, the Expansion Premises, and such Expansion Premises shall be added to the Premises, upon and subject to the terms of this Article&nbsp;33 and
<B>
<U STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Exhibit&nbsp;M
</U>
</B>
	.&#160; Landlord shall be deemed to have tendered possession of the Expansion Premises to Tenant, and Tenant shall be deemed to have accepted possession of the Expansion Premises, on the Expansion Premises Commencement Date, subject to Landlord&#146;s obligation hereunder to complete Punch List Items and to correct Expansion Premises Latent Defects (as defined in Exhibit&nbsp;M and subject to the terms thereof).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;33.2
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	The Fixed Rent payable in respect of the Expansion Premises shall be as set forth on &#147;
<U>
	Schedule A-2
</U>
	&#148; annexed hereto and made a part hereof.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;33.3
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Landlord shall not be obligated to perform any work with respect to the Expansion Premises or make any contribution to Tenant to prepare such Expansion Premises for Tenant&#146;s continued occupancy, other than Landlord&#146;s Expansion Premises Work, as set forth in Section&nbsp;33.6 below.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;33.4
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Following the Expansion Premises Commencement Date, the Expansion Premises shall be added to and be deemed to be a part of the Premises for all purposes of this Lease (except as otherwise provided in this Article&nbsp;33 and in respect of Landlord obligations relating to the Premises which accrued prior to the Expansion Premises Commencement Date).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;33.5
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Tenant has inspected the Expansion Premises and agrees (a)&nbsp;to accept possession of the Expansion Premises in its then condition on the Expansion Premises Commencement Date, subject to the terms of this Lease (including without limitation Section&nbsp;4.2, as applicable to the Expansion Premises) and Landlord agreeing to&#160; Substantially Complete Landlord&#146;s Expansion Premises Work, and (b)&nbsp;Landlord has no obligation to perform any work, supply any materials, incur any expense or make any alterations or improvements to the Expansion Premises or the Building in order to prepare the same for Tenant&#146;s initial occupancy on the Expansion Premises Commencement Date other than Landlord&#146;s Expansion Premises Work and the Base Building Work with respect to the Expansion Premises. Subject to Landlord&#146;s obligation to complete any Punch List Items in respect of the Expansion Premises and Expansion Premises Latent Defects, Tenant&#146;s occupancy of any portion of the Expansion Premises shall be conclusive evidence, as against Tenant, that Tenant has accepted possession of the Expansion Premises, in its then current condition and at the time such possession was taken, the Expansion Premises was in the condition required hereby.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;33.6
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Landlord will commence the performance of the Landlord&#146;s Expansion Premises Work reasonably promptly following the Expansion Premises Final Plans Approval
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
	90
<A NAME="A2231003ZEX-10_17_HTM_1015-2-KU-19_PB_90_113632_5796">
</A>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">

<!-- ZEQ.=1,SEQ=93,EFW="2231003",CP="2U, INC.",DN="3",CHK=612671,FOLIO='90',FILE="DISK131:[17ZAA2.17ZAA11502]1015-2-KU-19_ZAA11502.CHC",USER="HYUNG",CD='FEB 23 15:13 2017' -->
<A NAME="eolPage288"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Date (as defined in
<B>
<U STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Exhibit&nbsp;M
</U>
</B>
	attached hereto), subject to Tenant&#146;s compliance with the provisions of this Lease, and, will complete Landlord&#146;s Expansion Premises Work in a good and workmanlike manner consistent with the standards applicable to the Building.&#160; Landlord and its employees, contractors and agents shall have access to the Expansion Premises at all reasonable times for the performance of Landlord&#146;s Expansion Premises Work and for the storage of materials reasonably required in connection therewith (and for such time as may be reasonably required). Landlord shall diligently pursue completion of any and all Punch List Items within 60 days after Substantial Completion of Landlord&#146;s Expansion Premises Work (subject to Tenant Delay and Unavoidable Delay); provided that Landlord shall not unreasonably and materially interfere with Tenant&#146;s access to or installations or operations within the Expansion Premises.&#160;&#160; Except as otherwise expressly set forth herein to the contrary, there shall be no Rent abatement or allowance to Tenant for a diminution of rental value, no actual or constructive eviction of Tenant, in whole or in part, no relief from any of Tenant&#146;s other obligations under this Lease, and no liability on the part of Landlord, by reason of inconvenience, annoyance or injury to business arising from the performance of Landlord&#146;s Expansion Premises Work or the storage of any materials in connection therewith.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;33.7
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Landlord&#146;s performance of Landlord&#146;s Expansion Premises Work shall be performed pursuant to and in accordance with the terms and conditions of
<B>
	Exhibit&nbsp;M
</B>
	attached hereto. For purposes of
<B>
	Exhibit&nbsp;M
</B>
	, the &#147;Expansion Premises Contribution&#148; shall mean an amount in dollars which is obtained by multiplying (x)&nbsp;the quotient obtained by dividing (A)&nbsp;the number of full months and the fractional portion of any portion of a month in the period commencing on the Expansion Premises Commencement Date and ending on the Expiration Date and by (B)&nbsp;141 by (y)&nbsp;$75.00 by (z)&nbsp;26,500; provided, however, that if the Expansion Premises Commencement Date occurs after the Expansion Premises Outside Date, due solely to delays in the Substantial Completion of the Landlord&#146;s Expansion Premises Work caused solely by Landlord (and not caused by Tenant Delay and/or Unavoidable Delay), then the Expansion Premises Commencement Date for the purpose only of the calculation of the Expansion Premises Contribution described in this sentence shall deemed to be the date on which the Expansion Premises Commencement Date would have occurred but for the aforesaid delays caused by Landlord.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Section&nbsp;33.8
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Article&nbsp;33, provided no Event of Default then exists, then:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	if the Landlord&#146;s Expansion Premises Work is Substantially Completed on or prior to the twelve (12) month anniversary of the Commencement Date, Tenant shall receive a credit in the aggregate amount of $1,252,125 (the &#147;
<B>
	Expansion Premises Rent Credit
</B>
	&#148;) to be applied in equal monthly installments against Fixed Rent in respect of the Expansion Premises next due hereunder (i.e., such amount shall be applied to Fixed Rent for the Expansion Premises only); and
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	if the Landlord&#146;s Expansion Premises Work is substantially completed after the twelve (12) month anniversary of the Commencement Date but prior to the three (3)&nbsp;year anniversary of the Commencement Date, then Tenant shall receive a credit in the aggregate amount equal to the Pro Rata Share Expansion Premises Rent Credit (as hereinafter defined) to be applied in equal monthly installments against Fixed Rent in respect of the Expansion Premises next due hereunder.&#160;&#160; The &#147;Pro Rata Share Expansion Premises Rent Credit&#148; shall mean the product of (x)&nbsp;$1,715.24 multiplied by (y)&nbsp;the amount of days which occurs during the period commencing on the Expansion Premises Commencement Date and ending on the date which is the three (3)&nbsp;year anniversary of the Commencement Date.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
	91
<A NAME="A2231003ZEX-10_17_HTM_1015-2-KU-19_PB_91_113723_2897">
</A>

<!-- ZEQ.=1,SEQ=94,EFW="2231003",CP="2U, INC.",DN="3",CHK=73013,FOLIO='91',FILE="DISK131:[17ZAA2.17ZAA11502]1015-2-KU-19_ZAA11502.CHC",USER="HYUNG",CD='FEB 23 15:13 2017' -->
<A NAME="eolPage289"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ARTICLE&nbsp;34
<BR>
	EXPEDITED ARBITRATION
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	In the event of any dispute under this Lease or a Work Letter with respect to (a)&nbsp;any circumstance hereunder where Landlord agreed not to unreasonably withhold, delay or condition its consent, and Tenant claims that Landlord has in fact unreasonably withheld consent, delayed or conditioned it consent, (b)&nbsp;whether Landlord has Substantially Completed Landlord&#146;s Premises Work, the Roof Work or Landlord&#146;s Expansion Premises Work, as applicable, or any restoration of the Premises, (c)&nbsp;whether any particular items of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work, Landlord&#146;s Expansion Premises Work, or Roof Work as applicable, are Punch List Items, (d)&nbsp;whether there has been a Tenant Delay or Unavoidable Delay (including the commencement and duration thereof), (e)&nbsp;whether a new Rule&nbsp;and Regulation is reasonable, or (f)&nbsp;in any arbitration which, pursuant to the express provisions of this Lease, is governed by this Article&nbsp;34, either party may submit the dispute for resolution by arbitration in the City of New York in accordance with the City of New York under the Expedited Procedures provisions of the Commercial Arbitration Rules&nbsp;of the American Arbitration Association (&#147;
<B>
	AAA
</B>
	&#148;), except that the terms of this Article&nbsp;34 shall supersede any conflicting or otherwise inconsistent rules; provided, however, that with respect to any such arbitration under a Work Letter or with respect to Landlord&#146;s Premises Work, the Roof Work or Landlord&#146;s Expansion Premises Work (including whether there has been a Tenant Delay or Unavoidable Delay with respect to such work (including the commencement and duration thereof and whether such work has been Substantially Completed and whether an item is a Punch List item) (a &#147;
<B>
	Construction Dispute
</B>
	&#148;), (i)&nbsp;the arbitrator shall be a qualified, disinterested and impartial person who shall have had at least ten (10)&nbsp;years&#146; experience in the New York City commercial office market in a calling connected with the matter of the dispute, (ii)&nbsp;the AAA shall, within two (2)&nbsp;Business Days after such submission or application, select a single arbitrator meeting the requirements set forth in the following paragraph, (iii)&nbsp;the arbitration hearing shall commence two (2)&nbsp;Business Days after the selection of the arbitrator, (iv)&nbsp;the hearing shall be limited to a maximum duration of two (2)&nbsp;Business Days, with each party having no more than (A)&nbsp;two (2)&nbsp;hours to present its case, (B)&nbsp;two (2)&nbsp;hours to cross examine or interrogate persons supplying information or documentation on behalf of the other party, and (C)&nbsp;one (1)&nbsp;hour to summarize in a closing statement such party&#146;s case and (v)&nbsp;the arbitrator shall make a determination within three (3)&nbsp;Business Days after the conclusion of the hearing which determination shall be limited to a decision upon (1)&nbsp;whether Landlord acted reasonably in withholding its consent or approval or otherwise acted in an arbitrary or capricious manner where Landlord had a duty to act reasonably as expressly required by the terms hereof, or (2)&nbsp;the specific dispute presented to the arbitrator, as applicable. For all other disputes that are not Construction Disputes, provided the rules&nbsp;and regulations of the AAA so permit, (i)&nbsp;the AAA shall, within 2 Business Days after such submission or application, select a single arbitrator having at least ten (10)&nbsp;years&#146; experience in New York City in leasing (with respect to disputes related to failure to give consents to assignments or subleases) or with respect to all other matters experience in the New York City commercial office market in a calling connected with the matter of the dispute management of commercial properties similar to the Building, (ii)&nbsp;the arbitration hearing shall commence 2 Business Days thereafter and shall be limited to a total of seven hours on the date of commencement until completion, with each party having no more than a total of two hours to present its case and to cross-examine or interrogate persons supplying information or documentation on behalf of the other party, and (iii)&nbsp;the arbitrator shall make a determination within 3 Business Days after the conclusion of the presentation of Landlord&#146;s and Tenant&#146;s cases, which determination shall be limited to a decision upon (A)&nbsp;whether Landlord acted
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
	92
<A NAME="A2231003ZEX-10_17_HTM_1015-2-KU-19_PB_92_113741_3020">
</A>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="100%" NOSHADE ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="COLOR:#010101;">

<A NAME="eolPage290"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	reasonably in withholding its consent or approval, or (B)&nbsp;the specific dispute presented to the arbitrator, as applicable (and the arbitrator shall not be permitted to modify any of the terms of this Lease).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	In all cases, the arbitrator&#146;s determination shall be final and binding upon the parties, whether or not a judgment shall be entered in any court. All actions necessary to implement such decision shall be undertaken as soon as possible, but in no event later than 5 Business Days after the rendering of such decision. The arbitrator&#146;s determination may be entered in any court having jurisdiction thereof. All fees payable to the AAA for services rendered in connection with the resolution of the dispute shall be paid by the unsuccessful party.&#160; The arbitrator shall not be entitled to award monetary damages.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	This Section&nbsp;34 shall survive the expiration or sooner termination of this Lease.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	[
<I>
	signature page&nbsp;follows
</I>
	]
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">

<BR>
	HVAC DESIGN SPACE CONDITIONS
</FONT>
</B>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Landlord shall provide interior space temperatures of 70 degrees F +/- degrees that will be maintained during the heating seasons throughout the Premises without utilizing interior heat load, on (1)&nbsp;person per 150 rentable square feet and outside dry bulb temperature of 13.0 degrees. &nbsp;Landlord shall provide base building air conditioning capable of maintaining space temperatures 74 degrees F +/- 2 degrees and 50% relative humidity with an interior head load of 5.0 watts/rsf, no interior shading one (1)&nbsp;person per 150 rentable square feet, and outside mean coincident temperatures of 90 degrees F dry bulb, 73 degrees F wet bulb. &nbsp;Minimum 78 degrees F wb on the on the cooling tower.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Landlord shall provide a minimum ventilation of 75 CFM of toilet exhaust per fixture within the bathrooms&nbsp;based on Building standard open installation and one person per 150 rentable square feet.
</FONT>
</P>

<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	EXHIBIT&nbsp;B
<BR>
	DEFINITIONS
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Additional Rent:
</FONT>
</B>
	all sums other than Fixed Rent due and payable by Tenant to Landlord under this Lease.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Affiliate:&#160;
</FONT>
</B>
	Any person or entity which controls, is under common control with, or which is controlled by, the person or entity in question. For the purposes hereof, &#147;control&#148; shall be deemed to mean ownership of not less than 50% of all of the beneficial voting interests of such entity or the ability to direct the management thereof.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Base Rate:
</FONT>
</B>
	&#160; The annual rate of interest publicly announced from time to time by Citibank, N.A., or its successor, in New York, New York as its &#147;base rate&#148; (or such other term as may be used by Citibank, N.A., from time to time, for the rate presently referred to as its &#147;base rate&#148;).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Building Systems:
</FONT>
</B>
	&#160; The mechanical, electrical, plumbing, sanitary, sprinkler (including vertical standpipes), heating, ventilation air conditioning, security, life-safety, elevator and other service systems or facilities of the Building up to the point of connection of localized distribution to the Premises (excluding, however, supplemental HVAC systems of tenants, sprinklers and the horizontal distribution systems within or exclusively serving the Premises and by which mechanical, electrical, plumbing, sanitary, heating, ventilating and air conditioning, security, life-safety and other service systems are distributed from the base Building risers, feeders, panel boards,&nbsp;etc. for provision of such services to the Premises).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Building Standard
</FONT>
</B>
	: comparable office buildings in the close vicinity to the Building.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Business Days:
</FONT>
</B>
	&#160; All days, excluding Saturdays, Sundays and Observed Holidays.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Business Hours:
</FONT>
</B>
	8:00 a.m.&nbsp;to 6:00 p.m.&nbsp;on Business Days except Observed Holidays (and all other times are considered &#147;
<B>
	Overtime Periods
</B>
	&#148;).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Code:
</FONT>
</B>
	&#160; The Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended, and the regulations promulgated thereunder, as amended.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Common Areas:
</FONT>
</B>
	The lobby, sidewalk areas, and other similar areas of general access and the areas on individual multi-tenant floors in the Building devoted to corridors, elevator lobbies, restrooms, and other similar facilities serving the Premises.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Comparable Buildings:
</FONT>
</B>
	&#160; Office buildings in the Manhattan Midtown South area that are of comparable age and quality to the Building, taking into account all relevant factors.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Cost Per Kilowatt Hour:
</FONT>
</B>
	&#160; (a)&nbsp;The total cost for electricity incurred by Landlord to service the Building during a particular billing period (including energy charges, demand charges, surcharges, time-of-day charges, fuel adjustment charges, rate adjustment charges, taxes, rebates and any other factors used by the public utility company or other provider in computing its charges to Landlord) during such period, divided by (b)&nbsp;the total kilowatt hours purchased by Landlord to provide electricity to the Building during such period.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CPI
</FONT>
</B>
	:&#160; the&#160; Consumer Price Index for All Urban Consumers published by the Bureau of Labor Statistics of the United States Department of Labor, New York, N.Y. - Northeastern N.J. Area, All Items (1982-84=100), or any successor index thereto, appropriately adjusted.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Deficiency:
</FONT>
</B>
	&#160; The difference between (a)&nbsp;the Fixed Rent and Additional Rent for the period which otherwise would have constituted the unexpired portion of the Term, and (b)&nbsp;the net amount, if any, of rents collected under any reletting effected pursuant to the provisions of the Lease for any part of such period (after first deducting from such rents all expenses reasonably incurred by Landlord in connection with the termination of this Lease, Landlord&#146;s re-entry upon the Premises and such reletting, including repossession costs, brokerage commissions, reasonable attorneys&#146; fees and disbursements.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<B>

	Environmental Requirement
</FONT>
</U>
</B>
	: means any present and future Requirement and any amendments (whether common law, statute, rule, order, regulation or otherwise), permits and other requirements or guidelines of governmental authorities applicable to the Building or the Real Property and relating to the environment and environmental conditions or to any Hazardous Material (including, without limitation, CERCLA, 42 U.S.C. &#167; 9601 et seq., the Resource Conservation and Recovery Act of 1976, 42 U.S.C. &#167;6901 et seq., the Hazardous Materials Transportation Act, 49 U.S.C. &#167;1801 et seq., the Federal Water Pollution Control Act, 33 U.S.C. &#167;1251 et seq., the Clean Air Act, 33 U.S.C. &#167;7401 et seq., the Toxic Substances Control Act, 15 U.S.C. &#167;2601 et seq., the Safe Drinking Water Act, 42 U.S.C. &#167;300f et seq., the Emergency Planning and Community Right-To-Know Act, 42 U.S.C. &#167;1101 et seq., the Occupational Safety and Health Act, 29 U.S.C. &#167;651 et seq., and any so-called &#147;
<U>
	Super Fund
</U>
	&#148; or &#147;
<U>
	Super Lien
</U>
	&#148; law, any Requirement requiring the filing of reports and notices relating to hazardous substances, environmental laws administered by the Environmental Protection Agency, and any similar state and local Requirements, all amendments thereto and all regulations, orders, decisions, and decrees now or hereafter promulgated thereunder concerning the environment, industrial hygiene or public health or safety).
</P>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

</FONT>

</FONT>
</B>
	Either party&#146;s inability to fulfill or delay in fulfilling any of its non-monetary obligations under this Lease expressly or impliedly to be performed by such party or such party&#146;s inability to make or delay in making any repairs, additions, Alterations, improvements or decorations or such party&#146;s inability to supply or delay in supplying any equipment or fixtures, if such party&#146;s inability or delay is due to or arises by reason of strikes, labor troubles, or by any cause whatsoever beyond such party&#146;s reasonable control, including governmental preemption in connection with a national emergency, or shortages, or unavailability of labor, fuel, steam, water, electricity or materials, or delays caused by the other party or other tenants, mechanical breakdown, acts of God, enemy action, civil commotion, fire or other casualty (but specifically excluding delays caused by such party&#146;s financial difficulties).

	1.1
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

	As used herein &#147;
<B>
	Landlord&#146;s Premises Work
</B>
	&#148; shall mean, collectively the Premises Build-Out Work, the Base Building Work, the Primary Base Building Roof Work and
<B>
	&#147;Landlord&#146;s Secondary Roof Work
</B>
	&#148; shall mean, collectively the Tenant&#146;s Roof Work and the Secondary Base Building Roof Work. The purpose of this Work Letter is to set forth (i)&nbsp;how the interior improvements to the 9
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	th
</FONT>
	&#160;and 10
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	th
</FONT>
	&#160;Floor Premises which Tenant desires to have completed in connection with Tenant&#146;s initial occupancy of the 9
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	th
</FONT>
	&#160;and 10
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	th
</FONT>
	&#160;Floor Premises including, if selected by Tenant as part of Tenant&#146;s Plans, the construction of a sky light (the &#147;
<B>
	Skylight
</B>
	&#148;) on Tenant&#146;s Roof Deck Area as part of the 10
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	th
</FONT>
	&#160;Floor Premises ceiling (&#147;
<B>
	Premises Build-Out Work&#148;
</B>
	) are to be constructed, (ii)&nbsp;who will do the construction of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work and the Secondary Roof Work, and (iii)&nbsp;who will pay for the construction of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work and Landlord&#146;s Secondary Roof Work. Landlord&#146;s Premises Work shall include the Base Building Work and (i)&nbsp;the construction of an internal hydraulic lift and stairwell (collectively, the &#147;
<B>
	Stairway/Lift
</B>
	&#148;) from the 10th floor to Tenant&#146;s Roof Deck Area with a slab cut (the &#147;
<B>
	Slab Cut
</B>
	&#148;) to fit Stairway/Lift, (ii)&nbsp;the relocation of toilet exhaust that is on the way of path of egress to the left side fire stair, (iii)&nbsp;the construction of the Skylight, if applicable (i.e., if the applicable plans related thereto are timely submitted and approved by Landlord), (iv)&nbsp;the installation of a roof membrane (collectively, (i), (ii), (iii)&nbsp;(if applicable), and (iv)&nbsp;the &#147;
<B>
	Primary Base Building Roof Work
</B>
	&#148;). Landlord&#146;s Secondary Roof Work shall also include (i)&nbsp;the installation of a glass extension of the existing parapet wall, in the location set forth on
<B>
<U STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Exhibit&nbsp;K
</U>
</B>
<U>
	,
</U>
	which will comply with Requirements on the day such walls are installed, (ii)&nbsp;the installation of a barrier (the type of such barrier, including materials, height, color,&nbsp;etc. to be reasonably determined by Landlord in consultation with Tenant) between Tenant&#146;s Roof Deck Area and the remainder of the roof of the Building, (iii)&nbsp;the installation of a barrier (the type of such barrier including materials, height, color,&nbsp;etc. to be reasonably determined by Landlord in consultation with Tenant) between the Tenant Roof Deck Area and the Building equipment currently located on the roof of the Building, and (iv)&nbsp;the installation of pavers to cover the portion of the Tenant Roof Deck which will allow egress between Fire Stair A and Fire Stair B in the location set forth on
<B>
<U STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Exhibit&nbsp;K
</U>
</B>
	(collectively, (i), (ii), (iii), and (iv), the &#147;
<B>
	Secondary Base Building Roof Work
</B>
	&#148; and together with the Primary Base Building Roof Work, the &#147;
<B>
	Base Building Roof Work
</B>
	&#148;).&#160; For the avoidance of doubt, the Skylight, and all work related thereto, if applicable, shall be at Tenant&#146;s sole cost (but subject to reimbursement from Landlord&#146;s Contribution in accordance with the terms hereof).

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	2.2
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	The development of the Proposed Plans by Landlord&#146;s Architect is expected to be a collaborative process among Landlord, Tenant and Landlord&#146;s Architect, with Landlord reasonably approving progressive stages of plan completion (i.e., 25%, 50% and 75% CDs) at reasonable intervals before April&nbsp;25, 2017 (and at each interval giving Landlord at least ten (10)&nbsp;Business Days to review each such stage of drawings). Within ten (10)&nbsp;Business Days after Landlord receives a stage of Proposed Plans, Landlord shall either approve or disapprove same (or provide a request for more information), which approval or disapproval shall be in accordance with the standards set forth in Section&nbsp;5.1(a)&nbsp;of the Lease with respect to Landlord&#146;s approval or disapproval of Alterations (and any reasons for disapproval shall be referred to as, a &#147;
<B>
	Design Problem
</B>
	&#148;); provided that the failure of Landlord to respond to an initial submission within ten (10)&nbsp;Business Days or a resubmission after Landlord&#146;s comment within seven (7)&nbsp;Business Days shall be a Landlord Delay. If Landlord determines that a Design Problem exists, it shall return the Proposed Plans to Tenant together with a reasonably specific explanation of the applicable Design Problem. In such event, Tenant shall be required to make the revisions necessary (which revisions shall not expand the scope of the work but shall only be responses or corrections to Landlord&#146;s comments and/or the Design Problem(s)&nbsp;in question) in order to address Landlord&#146;s comments and correct the Design Problem(s)&nbsp;in full and, within five (5)&nbsp;Business Days thereafter, return the revised Proposed Plans to Landlord, which Landlord shall then approve or disapprove (or provide a request for more information) within seven (7)&nbsp;Business Days after receipt.&#160; Each subsequent stage of plans provided to Landlord shall be a logical progression of the immediately preceding stage of plans approved by Landlord (subject to Change Orders).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

</FONT>
	Landlord&#146;s standards for approval of a Change Order (as hereinafter defined) shall be subject to the standards set forth in Section&nbsp;2.2 above. Landlord and Tenant shall exercise all reasonable diligence to cooperate in the expeditious pursuit of plan and contractor approval and the award of the construction contract and subcontracts in connection with Landlord&#146;s Premises Work and the Secondary Roof Work, including awarding portions of the construction contracts and obtaining permits based upon partially complete Proposed Plans. Landlord&#146;s Architect and the general contractor and construction manager shall have no obligation to self-certify permit applications and/or inspections.

<A NAME="eolPage306"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	responsible for all the costs and expenses to design and complete the Base Building Work and the Base Building Roof Work. Landlord shall also pay for the Premises Build-Out Work and the Tenant Roof Work depicted on the Final Plans (and all architectural costs, engineering costs, general contractor costs, and the cost of all local and state filing fees and permits required to be obtained in order to perform such work) to the extent and only to the extent of an aggregate expenditure with respect to all the aforementioned costs in an amount not to exceed $3,975,000.00 (&#147;
<B>
	Landlord&#146;s Contribution
</B>
	&#148;). Tenant shall pay for the cost of any work or materials depicted on the Final Plans and/or other costs directly related to the Premises Build-Out Work, including, without limitation all architectural costs of Landlord&#146;s Architect, engineering costs, project management fees, general contractor costs, and the costs of all filing fees and permits required by any Governmental Authority and incurred by Landlord in connection with the Premises Build-Out Work and Tenant&#146;s Roof Work, which are in excess of Landlord&#146;s Contribution or the Roof Work Contribution, as applicable (&#147;
<B>
	Tenant&#146;s Contribution
</B>
	&#148;), which excess shall be paid in accordance with the following: (1)&nbsp;34% of the then estimated (based upon the sum of the winning bids or the amount of the fixed priced or GMP type contract as reasonably determined by Landlord) Tenant&#146;s Contribution shall be paid within ten (10)&nbsp;days after submission to Tenant of a reasonably detailed summary with applicable supporting documentation from Landlord or Construction Manager but no earlier than the earlier of&#160; awarding or selecting the winning bids for substantially all the Premises Build-Out Work (excluding the Expansion Premises) or sooner finalizing of a fixed price or GMP type contract between Landlord and the Construction Manager or general contractor, (2)&nbsp;33% of the then estimated (based upon the sum of the winning bids or the amount of the fixed priced or GMP type contract as reasonably determined by Landlord) Tenant&#146;s Contribution shall be paid within ten (10)&nbsp;days after 50% of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work is Substantially Completed (as reasonably determined Landlord and certified by Landlord&#146;s Architect), and (3)&nbsp;the balance of Tenant&#146;s Contribution shall be paid within ten (10)&nbsp;days after the earlier of (x)&nbsp;Substantial Completion of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work and (y)&nbsp;Tenant&#146;s occupancy of the Premises for the conduct of business. The payments to be made by Tenant as provided in this Section&nbsp;3.2 shall be collectible in the same manner as Additional Rent under the Lease, whether or not the Term of the Lease shall have commenced. The Tenant Contribution shall be immediately payable upon an Event Default. All Change Costs shall be paid as set forth in Section&nbsp;6 below.
</FONT>

	3.3

<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">

	Landlord shall submit to Tenant, as soon as reasonably practicable, the total estimated cost of the Premises Build-Out Work and Tenant&#146;s Roof Work (which shall be updated regularly during the development of the Proposed Plans as provided above).

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">

	3.4
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	To the extent that the Final Plans include any work to the roof which is not Base Building Roof Work (&#147;
<B>
	Tenant Roof Work
</B>
	&#148;), Landlord shall perform such Tenant Roof Work as part of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work. Upon Tenant&#146;s written request made within fifteen (15) days following approval of the Proposed Plans, Landlord shall make available to Tenant up to an additional amount equal to $300,000.00 (the &#147;
<B>
	Roof Work Contribution
</B>
	&#148;) and in such event Landlord&#146;s Contribution shall include the Roof Work Contribution,
<I>
	provided
</I>
	,
<I>
	however
</I>
	, that the Roof Work Contribution shall be applied to the costs of Tenant Roof Work and the design, purchase and construction of the Skylight only (and any amount not so applied shall be deducted from Landlord&#146;s Contribution). The Primary Base Building Roof Work, Secondary Base Building Roof Work, and the Tenant Roof Work, and the shall be collectively referred to herein as the &#147;
<B>
	Roof Work
</B>
	&#148;.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">

	3.5
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Landlord has hired, and Tenant approves of, CBRE,&nbsp;Inc. to act as project manager (&#147;
<B>
	Project Manager
</B>
	&#148;) to assist with the planning and performance of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work. Project Manager shall be paid an amount equal to 3% of the cost of the Premises Build-Out Work and Tenant&#146;s Roof&#160; Work (the &#147;
<B>
	Project Manager Fee
</B>
	&#148;), which shall be
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	deducted from (as applicable) Landlord&#146;s Contribution or the Roof Work Contribution. For the avoidance of doubt, it is agreed that Landlord shall not receive a supervisory or override fee in respect of the performance of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work and Tenant&#146;s Roof Work.

	3.7
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

	Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained herein or in the Lease, during the performance of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work or Tenant&#146;s Roof Work, the cost of any overtime freight elevator use shall be limited to the actual costs Landlord incurs for the use thereof (i.e., there shall be no additional mark-up in addition to such actual costs). In that regard, Landlord shall use the services of the overtime freight elevators in a reasonable and customary manner and for reasonable and customary needs in connection with prudent construction practices for similar projects.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">

	3.8.

<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">

	Tenant shall be responsible for $100,000.00 of the cost and expense for any hoists, exterior cranes or sidewalk bridges with respect to Landlord&#146;s Premises Work or the Roof Work that is erected or installed in connection with Landlord&#146;s Premises Work or the Roof Work (collectively, &#147;
<B>
	Hoist Costs
</B>
	&#148;).&#160; Landlord shall be responsible for Hoist Costs in excess of $100,000.00.

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	3.9
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Subject to the Hoist Costs and other costs specifically and expressly provided for herein (e.g., costs related to Change Orders as provided herein), Landlord shall be solely responsible for all costs and expense incurred in connection with designing and completing the Base Building Work and the Base Building Roof Work (other than the design and construction of the Skylight which, except for the cost of the roof membrane and its interface with the Skylight, shall be at Tenant&#146;s cost, subject to the following sentence), including, without limitation, hard costs, engineering fees, Landlord&#146;s Architect&#146;s fees, and the Construction Management Fee. Subject to Landlord&#146;s Contribution (with respect to the Premises Build-Out Work) and Landlord&#146;s Roof Contribution (with respect to Tenant&#146;s Roof Work), Tenant shall be solely responsible for the cost and expense of completing the Premises Build-Out Work and Tenant&#146;s Roof Work, including, without limitation, hard costs, engineering fees, Landlord&#146;s Architect&#146;s fees, and the Construction Management Fee related thereto, in addition to the design and construction fees related to the Skylight. Landlord shall be solely responsible for performing all of the foregoing.&#160; For the avoidance of doubt, any incremental costs incurred by Landlord in in connection with the cost of the roof membrane and its interface with the Skylight which would not have been incurred had a Skylight not been part of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work, shall be at Tenant&#146;s cost.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

	3.10.

	Within 30 days following the Substantial Completion of Landlord&#146;s Work and Landlord&#146;s Roof Work and 60 days after final completion of the same, Landlord, upon Tenant&#146;s request, shall provide Tenant with a preliminary accounting and then final accounting in reasonable detail, together with all reasonable backup and supporting materials reasonably requested by Tenant, prepared by or for Landlord for all amounts incurred in connection with such Landlord&#146;s Work and Landlord&#146;s Roof Work (but excluding the Base Building Work and the Primary Base Building Roof Work).&#160; Upon mutual agreement of the finality thereof, there shall be adjustments between Landlord and Tenant to the end that Landlord or Tenant has underpaid or overpaid any amount due from such party pursuant to the terms of this Work Letter. Any overpayment by Tenant shall be payable by Landlord to Tenant within thirty (30) days after the determination thereof. In the event that Tenant and Landlord are unable to agree on the finality of any adjustments after using good faith efforts to resolve the same for at least thirty (30) days and after Tenant sends in writing a reasonably detailed explanation of the amounts in dispute, then Tenant and Landlord shall appoint an Approved Examiner to resolve any such adjustments, whose determination shall be binding upon the parties. Any underpayment by

	4.1
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	If Landlord shall be delayed in Substantially Completing Landlord&#146;s Premises Work as a result of any act, neglect, failure or omission of Tenant, its agents, servants, employees, contractors or sub-contractors, including, without limitation, any of the following, such delay shall be a &#147;
<B>
	Tenant Delay
</B>
	&#148; to the extent such delay actually results in a delay in the Substantial Completion of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;

<A NAME="eolPage309"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	To the extent that Tenant submits design drawings or other reasonably detailed to plans to Landlord prior to the submission of the Proposed Plans, Landlord shall use reasonable efforts to delineate items depicted thereon which may be reasonably expected to be long lead items. If long lead items are identified by Landlord, Landlord agrees to use reasonable efforts to mitigate the length of time required to obtain and/or install such items, as applicable, or suggest reasonable alternatives and materials that may not be long lead items.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Tenant acknowledges and agrees that notwithstanding which party engages Landlord&#146;s Architect to prepare construction drawings for Landlord&#146;s Premises Work, the time periods and dates for which plans are required to be delivered shall be binding upon the parties even if delays are attributable to Landlord&#146;s Architect, but subject to delays caused solely by Landlord&#146;s wrongful or negligent acts or material changes unilaterally requested by Landlord to Tenant&#146;s Premises Work and not in response to Tenant&#146;s changes.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	4.2
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Tenant shall pay to Landlord a sum equal to any actual out-of-pocket incremental additional cost to Landlord in completing Landlord&#146;s Premises Work resulting from (i)&nbsp;any Tenant Delay, and/or (ii)&nbsp;on account of any Change Orders (but not any increase in Hoist Costs). Any such sums shall be in addition to any sums payable pursuant to
<B>
	Sections 3.3, 3.4 and 3.5
</B>
	hereof and shall be paid to Landlord within 10 Business Days after Landlord submits an invoice to Tenant therefor.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	4.3
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	No Tenant Delay shall be deemed to have occurred unless and until Landlord has provided written notice to Tenant specifying the action or inaction that constitutes a Tenant Delay, except to the extent that Tenant has actual notice or constructive notice (e.g., response time frames pursuant to the terms hereof or circumstances for which the Lease expressly states same is a Tenant Delay) of Tenant Delay, in which case no such notice is required. If such action or inaction is not cured within two (2)&nbsp;Business Days after receipt of such notice, then a Tenant Delay as set forth in such notice shall be deemed to have occurred commencing as of the date such notice is received and continuing for the number of days the substantial completion of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work was in fact delayed as a result of such action or inaction (and if no notice is required as aforesaid, then the applicable Tenant Delay shall be deemed to have occurred commencing as of the date of such occurrence of Tenant Delay and continue for the number of days the substantial completion of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work was in fact delayed as a result of such action or inaction).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	5.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Entry by Tenant and Its Agents; Designation of Tenant&#146;s Construction Agent
</B>
	.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	5.1
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Except for Early Access Work, as provided in Section&nbsp;7 of this Work Letter or as otherwise permitted by Landlord, neither Tenant nor its agents, employers, invitees or independent contractors shall enter the Premises during the performance of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work within the 9
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	th
</FONT>
	&#160;Floors and 10
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	th
</FONT>
	&#160;Floors. Tenant hereby designates Jason Peterman as its authorized agent (&#147;
<B>
	Tenant&#146;s Construction Agent
</B>
	&#148;) for the purpose of submitting to Landlord and authorizing any Change Orders and for the purpose of consulting with Landlord as to any and all aspects of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	5.2
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	If Tenant shall enter upon the Premises or any other part of the Building prior to the Commencement Date, as may be above permitted by Landlord, Tenant shall indemnify and save Landlord harmless from and against any and all Losses arising from or claimed to arise as a result of (i)&nbsp;any act, neglect or failure to act (where Tenant had a duty to
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<A NAME="eolPage310"></A>

<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	act) of Tenant or anyone entering the Premises or Building with Tenant&#146;s permission, or (ii)&nbsp;any other reason whatsoever arising out of Tenant&#146;s entry upon the Premises or Building.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	6.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Change Orders
</B>
	.&#160; If Tenant requests any change, addition or deletion to the Final Plans (collectively referred to as a &#147;
<B>
	Change Order
</B>
	&#148;), then a request for such Change Order shall be submitted to Landlord for Landlord&#146;s approval. Landlord shall not unreasonably withhold its consent to any requested Change Order in accordance with the standards set forth in Section&nbsp;2.2 of this Work Letter, and grant or deny its consent thereto within (x)&nbsp;five (5)&nbsp;Business Days after Landlord&#146;s receipt of a Change Order which satisfies all of the Reasonable Alteration Conditions, or (y)&nbsp;ten (10)&nbsp;Business Days after Landlord&#146;s receipt of a Change Order which does not satisfy all of the Reasonable Alteration Conditions and if such change is material or extensive, such additional time as may be reasonably required to respond based on the magnitude of such change. Any Design Problem shall be handled in accordance with the correction procedures established therefor in Section&nbsp;2.2 of this Work Letter. If a Change Order is approved by Landlord, Landlord shall, together with its notice of approval, notify Tenant of its reasonable, good faith estimate (collectively,
<B>
	&#147;Landlord&#146;s Change Estimate&#148;
</B>
	) of: (i)&nbsp;the cost (or savings) which will be chargeable to Tenant as a result of such Change Order, which cost (or savings) shall the actual additional out-of-pocket incremental cost (or savings) of the Change Order (without additional mark-up paid directly to Landlord), taking into account any costs savings as the result of such Change Order and payable by Tenant to Landlord in connection with such Change Order (&#147;
<B>
	Change Cost
</B>
	&#148;) and (ii)&nbsp;the delay, if any, in Substantial Completion of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work (which shall include, without limitation, any additional time taken to renew such Change Order and revised plans and/or to obtain required permits or file documents with the NYC DOB, which Landlord shall diligently pursue) by reason of such Change Order (and shall be deemed a Tenant Delay for such delay period subject to Landlord&#146;s ). Such Change Cost shall include, without limitation, all actual out of pocket costs reasonably incurred by Landlord as a result of any such delay in completion of the Landlord&#146;s Premises Work directly resulting from such Change Order, if any, and so specified in Landlord&#146;s Change Estimate. Tenant shall within two (2)&nbsp;Business Days after Landlord&#146;s delivery to Tenant of Landlord&#146;s Change Estimate, notify Landlord in writing whether it desires to proceed with such Change Order. Tenant shall not make any changes to (or that affect beyond a de minimis extent) Landlord&#146;s Base Building Work. If such Change Orders increase the cost of constructing the Landlord&#146;s Premises Work shown on the Final Plans, such cost shall be added to the cost of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work and paid by the parties in accordance with this
<B>
	Exhibit&nbsp;C
</B>
	, subject in all events to the Landlord&#146;s Contribution. Landlord may, in the exercise of its sole and absolute discretion, disapprove any proposed Change Orders which do not satisfy all of the Reasonable Alteration Conditions. All reasonable and actual delays to the Substantial Completion Landlord&#146;s Premises Work resulting from a Change Order submission review (whether or not Landlord proceeds with such change) shall be deemed a Tenant Delay.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	7.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Construction Process
</B>
	.
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	It is intended that performance of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work be pursuant to a so-called &#147;Open Book&#148; process, whereby representatives of Landlord, Landlord&#146;s Construction Manager and Tenant if same are provided (collectively, the &#147;
<B>
	Work Parties
</B>
	&#148;) will work jointly and in good faith to timely prosecute the construction process to completion in accordance with the terms of the Lease. The Work Parties shall endeavor to meet not less than bi-weekly to review the progress of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work and promptly resolve any issues that arise during the course thereof. Minutes shall be recorded at all meetings of the Work Parties and cover, to the extent applicable the following:
</P>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

	(i)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	review of contractor&#146;s work schedule to anticipate items of contractor&#146;s work next falling due;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;

	9.1
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">

	This Work Letter shall not be deemed applicable to any additional space added to the original Premises at any time or from time to time, whether by any options under the Lease or otherwise, or to any portion of the original Premises or any additions thereto in the event of a renewal or extension of the initial term of the Lease, whether by any options under the Lease or otherwise, unless expressly so provided in the Lease or any amendment or supplement thereto.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">

	9.2
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">

</FONT>
	The failure by Tenant to pay any monies due Landlord pursuant to this Work Letter within 10 Business Days (or such longer period, if applicable) of the date due shall be deemed an Event of Default under the Lease for which Landlord shall be entitled to exercise all remedies available to Landlord for nonpayment of Rent and Landlord, may, if it so elects, discontinue construction of Landlord&#146;s Work until all such sums are paid and Tenant has otherwise cured such Event of Default (and any delay in the performance of Landlord&#146;s Premises Work resulting therefrom shall be deemed to be a Tenant Delay). All late payments shall bear interest at the Interest Rate.

	9.3
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">

</FONT>
	Landlord&#146;s Work shall be performed by Landlord in material compliance with all Requirements, in a good and workman manner, and in material compliance with the Final Plans.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	9.4
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Upon Tenant&#146;s written request made within fifteen (15) days following the date the Final Plans are approved, TIME BEING OF THE ESSENCE, Landlord shall make available to Tenant up to an additional amount equal to $1,987,500.00 (the &#147;
<B>
	Additional Landlord&#146;s Contribution
</B>
	&#148;) and in such event Landlord&#146;s Contribution shall include the Additional Landlord&#146;s Contribution. If Tenant requests the Additional Landlord&#146;s Contribution, then Tenant shall pay to Landlord a monthly sum, which shall be deemed Additional Rent and paid together with Tenant&#146;s payment of Fixed Rent (without abatement) each month during the Term, equal to the amount necessary to amortize Additional Landlord&#146;s Contribution on a straight line basis over the then remaining Term in equal monthly installments with interest thereon at eight percent (8%) per annum. Upon the termination of this Lease prior to the Expiration Date, the entire unamortized portion of the Additional Landlord&#146;s Contribution shall immediately become due and owing.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

	9.5
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Any defect in Landlord&#146;s Work and the Roof Work (i)&nbsp;of which Tenant has notified Landlord within 12 months after the Premises and the Tenant&#146;s Roof Deck Area has
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	been respectively delivered to Tenant with all of Landlord&#146;s Work and Roof Work (as applicable) substantially complete (each, a &#147;
<B>
	Work Delivery Date
</B>
	&#148;), and (ii)&nbsp;that had not been caused by a Tenant Party (which for the purposes of this Section&nbsp;9.5, shall not include Gensler), shall be referred to herein as a &#147;
<B>
	Latent Defect
</B>
	&#148;. Landlord shall remedy any Latent Defects provided Tenant notifies Landlord thereof within one year of the Applicable Work Delivery Date. If a defect in Landlord&#146;s Work or Roof Work is discovered which is not a Latent Defect, and such defect is covered by a warranty for Landlord&#146;s Work and the Roof Work which warranty has not been assigned to Tenant, then Landlord, at its cost, so long as such defect was not caused by a Tenant Party, shall use commercially reasonable efforts to enforce such warranty (but shall have no obligation to commence a lawsuit related thereto).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	9.6
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Landlord shall use commercially reasonable efforts to obtain market equipment and construction warranties from suppliers supplying materials and equipment as part of Landlord&#146;s Work and the Roof Work and contractors performing Landlord&#146;s Work and the Roof Work to the extent such warranties are typically provided by such trades To the extent obtained as part of Landlord&#146;s Work and Roof Work and assignable, Landlord shall assign to Tenant any&#160; warranties from contractors or suppliers to the extent Tenant is responsible for maintaining and repairing the equipment, materials or work the subject of such warranty, pursuant to the terms of the Lease.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	10.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Base Building Work
</B>
	.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	10.1
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Landlord&#146;s Work shall include the following work (the &#147;
<B>
	Base Building Work
</B>
	&#148;), which shall be performed at Landlord&#146;s sole cost, in accordance with the terms hereof:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 17.1PT;TEXT-INDENT:-17.1PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Landlord shall construct Building standard men&#146;s and women&#146;s ADA compliant bathrooms in each floor of the 9
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	th
</FONT>
	&#160;and 10
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	th
</FONT>
	&#160;Floor Premises.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 17.1PT;TEXT-INDENT:-17.1PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	2.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	The floors of the 9
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	th
</FONT>
	&#160;and 10
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	th
</FONT>
	&#160;Floor Premises shall be repaired or patched as reasonably required (as determined by Landlord) and Landlord will use reasonable efforts to remove any significant and material imperfections to accommodate Tenant&#146;s floor covering.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 17.1PT;TEXT-INDENT:-17.1PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	3.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Landlord shall perform required and necessary fireproofing (including to penetrations) and enclosure any exposed structural steel.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT 17.1PT;TEXT-INDENT:-17.1PT;">

	4.
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
